label: organic acid
description: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.

label: organic molecular entity
description: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

label: one-carbon compound
description: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).

label: epoxy hydrocarbon
description: Mutation induced by exposure to epoxy hydrocarbon.
synonyms: mutation induced by epoxy hydrocarbon exposure

label: chemical entity
description: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

label: epoxide
description: Any cyclic ether in which the oxygen atom forms part of a 3-membered ring.

label: atom
description: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

label: metal sulfate
description: Sulfate salts where the cation is a metal ion.

label: inorganic molecular entity
description: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

label: boric acids
description: Hydroxy boron compounds of general formula BxOyHz.

label: sodium bisulphite
synonyms: mutation induced by sodium bisulphite exposure

label: sodium fluoride
synonyms: mutation induced by sodium fluoride exposure

label: nucleobase analogue
description: A molecule that can substitute for a normal nucleobase in nucleic acids.

label: enzyme inhibitor
synonyms: mutation induced by enzyme inhibitor exposure

label: enzyme inhibitor
description: A compound or agent that combines with an enzyme in such a manner as to prevent the normal substrate-enzyme combination and the catalytic reaction.

label: dicarboxylic acid
description: An oxoacid containing two carboxy groups.

label: molecular entity
description: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

label: intercalating agent
synonyms: mutation induced by intercalating agent exposure

label: pyrimidines
description: Any compound having a pyrimidine as part of its structure.

label: nucleoside
description: An N-glycosyl compound that has both a nucleobase, normally adenine, guanine, xanthine, thymine, cytosine or uracil, and either a ribose or deoxyribose as functional parents.

label: quinacrine mustard
synonyms: mutation induced by quinacrine mustard exposure

label: nitrogen mustard
synonyms: mutation induced by nitrogen mustard exposure

label: nitrogen mustard
description: Compounds having two beta-haloalkyl groups bound to a nitrogen atom, as in (X-C2H2-C2H2)2NR.

label: aminoacridine
description: Acridines which are substituted in any position by one or more amino groups or substituted amino groups.

label: response to external stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an external stimulus.

label: response to stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell or organism.

label: vinyl carbamate
synonyms: mutation induced by vinyl carbamate exposure

label: carbamate ester
description: An ester of carbamic acid.

label: carbamate
description: An amino-acid anion that has formula CH2NO2.

label: intercalator
description: A role played by a chemical agent which exhibits the capability of occupying space between DNA base pairs due to particular properties in size, shape and charge. Intercalation of chemical compounds in DNA helix can result in replication errors (shift, mutation) or DNA damages.

label: mitomycin C
synonyms: mutation induced by mitomycin C exposure

label: heteroatomic molecular entity
description: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

label: polyatomic entity
description: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

label: response to wounding
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating damage to the organism.

label: response to stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis, usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: hycanthon methanesulfonate
synonyms: mutation induced by hycanthon methanesulfonate exposure

label: alkylating agent
synonyms: mutation induced by alkylating agent exposure

label: bis(2-chloroethyl) sulfide
synonyms: mutation induced by bis(2-chloroethyl) sulfide exposure

label: organochlorine compound
description: An organochlorine compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chlorine bond.

label: nitroso compound
description: Compounds having the nitroso group, -NO, attached to carbon, or to another element, most commonly nitrogen or oxygen.

label: ethyl methanesulfonate
synonyms: mutation induced by ethyl methanesulfonate exposure

label: locomotion
description: Self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another.

label: biological_process
description: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.

label: organofluorine compound
description: An organofluorine compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-fluorine bond.

label: growth
description: The increase in size or mass of an entire organism, a part of an organism or a cell.

label: origin of mutation
description: Describes the origin of the mutation that causes a phenotype.

label: alkylating agent
description: Highly reactive chemical that introduces alkyl radicals into biologically active molecules and thereby prevents their proper functioning. It could be used as an antineoplastic agent, but it might be very toxic, with carcinogenic, mutagenic, teratogenic, and immunosuppressant actions. It could also be used as a component of poison gases.

label: diethyl sulfate
synonyms: mutation induced by diethyl sulfate exposure

label: radio waves
description: Mutation induced by exposure to radio waves.
synonyms: mutation induced by radio waves irradiation

label: non-ionizing radiation
description: Mutation induced by exposure to non-ionizing radiation.

label: stratosphere
description: Mutation induced by exposure to the stratosphere.

label: supersonic
description: Mutation induced by exposure to supersonic radiation.

label: U.V.
description: Mutation induced by exposure to U.V. radiation.

label: response to abiotic stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an abiotic (non-living) stimulus.

label: magnetic field
description: Mutation induced by exposure to a magnetic field.
synonyms: mutation induced by magnetic field irradiation

label: response to gravity
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a gravitational stimulus.

label: nervous system
description: All the nerve centers and nerve fibers in the central, visceral and peripheral nervous systems.

label: organ system
description: A division of the whole organism into specialized systems.

label: urethane
description: A carbamate ester that has formula C3H7NO2.

label: X ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to X rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by X ray irradiation

label: ionizing radiation
description: Mutation induced by exposure to ionizing radiation.

label: irradiation
description: Mutation induced by exposure to radiation.

label: male
description: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

label: Bevatron
description: Mutation induced by treatment in a Bevatron.

label: female
description: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that only produces gametes that can be fertilised by male gametes.

label: deuteron
description: Mutation induced by exposure to deuteron radiation.

label: ICR-170
description: An acridine that has formula C21H27Cl4N3O.

label: increased frequency
description: A frequency which is relatively high.

label: frequency
description: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

label: increased rate
description: A rate which is relatively high.

label: neutron
description: Mutation induced by exposure to neutron radiation.

label: pupal stage
description: The pupal stage starts once larval/pupal apolysis is complete as indicated by the expulsion of the larval armature. Early in this stage, the legs and wings reach full extension along the abdomen. The stage ends when the pupal cuticle separates from the underlying epidermis (pupal/adult apolysis), and the eye cup becomes yellow at its periphery. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 32 hours. (132.2-164.3 hours after egg laying; 12.2-44.3 hours after puparium formation).

label: life stage
description: A temporal subdivision of a Drosophila life, delimited by major transitions in the circumstances of the organism, such as: fertilisation; hatching; pupal ecdysis; eclosion.

label: pharate adult stage
description: The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis , i.e.- from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 55.7 hours (164.3-220 hours after egg laying; 44.3-100 hours after puparium formation).

label: P-stage
description: The stage of the Drosophila life-cycle from the formation of the puparium (beginning of the prepupal stage) to eclosion.

label: prepupal stage
description: The prepupal stage begins at puparium formation and ends when larval/pupal apolysis is complete, as indicated by the completion of imaginal head sac eversion and the expulsion of the oral armature of the larva. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 12 hours. (120-132.2 hours after egg laying; 0-12.2 hours after puparium formation).

label: Janus Green B chloride
description: An organic chloride salt that has formula C30H31ClN6.

label: decreased frequency
description: A frequency which is relatively low.

label: decreased rate
description: A rate which is relatively low.

label: 252Cf fission neutron
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 252Cf fission neutron radiation.
synonyms: mutation induced by 252Cf fission neutron irradiation

label: 32P
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 32P radiation.

label: 3H
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 3H radiation.

label: 3H-deoxycytidine
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 3H-deoxycytidine radiation.

label: 3H-thymidine
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 3H-thymidine radiation.

label: flavanones
description: Members of the class of flavans with a 3,4-dihydro-2-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran-4-one skeleton and its substituted derivatives.

label: system process
description: A multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system. An organ system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a biological objective.

label: multicellular organismal process
description: Any biological process, occurring at the level of a multicellular organism, pertinent to its function.

label: developmental process involved in reproduction
description: A developmental process in which a progressive change in the state of some part of an organism specifically contributes to its ability to form offspring.

label: developmental process
description: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

label: reproductive process
description: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals by one or two organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: localization
description: Any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported, tethered to or otherwise maintained in a specific location. In the case of substances, localization may also be achieved via selective degradation.

label: regionalization
description: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of an axis or axes in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place or in which cells interpret a specific environment.

label: pattern specification process
description: Any developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within an organism to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.

label: process quality
description: A quality which inheres in an process.

label: quality
description: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities.

label: 60Co gamma ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 60Co gamma rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by 60Co gamma ray irradiation

label: gamma ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to gamma rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by gamma ray irradiation

label: larval stage
description: The stage of the Drosophila life-cycle from hatching to the beginning of puparium formation.

label: embryonic stage
description: The stage of the Drosophila life-cycle from fertilisation to hatching.

label: 137Cs gamma ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 137Cs gamma rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by 137Cs gamma ray irradiation

label: first instar larval stage
description: The first larval instar begins at hatching and ends at the first larval molt. Anterior spiracles are not yet present; posterior spiracles have two openings each. Salivary glands are very small and all cells are uniform in size. Mouth hooks typically have one tooth. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 25 hours (24-49 hours after egg laying; 0-25 hours after hatching).

label: second instar larval stage
description: The second larval instar begins at the first larval molt and ends at the second larval molt. Larvae are actively feeding and crawling in the food. Distinct anterior spiracles are present as enlargements at the end of the tracheal trunk, but not open to the outside; posterior spiracles have three openings each, and four groups of small unbranched hairs. The salivary glands extend to the first abdominal segment, and have cells that are uniform in size. Mouth hooks typically have two or three teeth. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 23 hours (49-72 hours after egg laying; 25-48 hours after hatching).

label: 226Ra alpha ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to 226Ra alpha rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by 226Ra alpha ray irradiation

label: regulation of gene expression, epigenetic
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression; the process is mitotically or meiotically heritable, or is stably self-propagated in the cytoplasm of a resting cell, and does not entail a change in DNA sequence.

label: regulation of gene expression
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA or circRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA or circRNA into protein. Protein maturation is included when required to form an active form of a product from an inactive precursor form.

label: physical object quality
description: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: alpha ray
description: Mutation induced by exposure to alpha rays.
synonyms: mutation induced by alpha ray irradiation

label: third instar larval stage
description: The third larval instar begins at the second larval molt and ends at puparium formation. Anterior spiracles are open to the outside; posterior spiracles have three openings each, and four groups of large branched hairs. The salivary glands extend to the second abdominal segment, with cells larger in the posterior than in the anterior of the gland. Mouth hooks typically have 9-12 teeth. About 24 hours before pupariation (at 25 degree C), larvae stop feeding and climb away from their food. Duration at 25 degrees C: approximately 48 hours (72-120 hours after egg laying; 48-96 hours after hatching).

label: photoperiodism
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a period of light or dark of a given length, measured relative to a particular duration known as the 'critical day length'. The critical day length varies between species.

label: response to light stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus, electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light.

label: mariner activity
description: Mutation induced by the transposable activity caused by mariner, a DNA transposable element. The mariner element is 1.3 kilobases in length with 28 base pairs inverted terminal repeats. It specifically targets TA dinucleotides and generates a flanking duplication of these two bases upon insertion. Mobilization is induced by the activity of the mariner transposase.

label: transposable element activity
description: Mutation induced by the mobilization of a transposable element.
synonyms: mutation induced by transposable element activity

label: entrainment of circadian clock
description: The synchronization of a circadian rhythm to environmental time cues such as light.

label: regulation of circadian rhythm
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a circadian rhythm. A circadian rhythm is a biological process in an organism that recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label: caffeine
description: A trimethylxanthine in which the three methyl groups are located at positions 1, 3, and 7.

label: gypsy element activity
description: Mutation induced by transposable activity caused by the gypsy retrovirus. The gypsy element is a 7.5 kilobases in length with 482 base pairs terminal repeats. Mobilization is induced by the activity of the gypsy element transposase.
synonyms: mutation induced by gypsy element activity

label: nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
description: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.
synonyms: cellular nucleobase, nucleoside, nucleotide and nucleic acid metabolic process

label: cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving various organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds, as carried out by individual cells.

label: primary metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving those compounds which are formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

label: cellular aromatic compound metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving aromatic compounds, any organic compound characterized by one or more planar rings, each of which contains conjugated double bonds and delocalized pi electrons, as carried out by individual cells.

label: organic cyclic compound metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic cyclic compound.

label: heterocycle metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving heterocyclic compounds, those with a cyclic molecular structure and at least two different atoms in the ring (or rings).

label: purines
description: Any compound containing purine as part of its structure.

label: piggyBac activity
description: Mutation induced by the transposable activity caused by piggyBac, a DNA transposable element. The piggyBac is 2.5 kilobases in length with 13 base pairs inverted terminal repeats. It specifically targets TTAA dinucleotides and generates a flanking duplication of these 4 base pairs upon insertion. Mobilization is induced by the activity of the piggyBac transposase.

label: dormancy process
description: A developmental process in which dormancy (sometimes called a dormant state) is induced, maintained or broken. Dormancy is a suspension of most physiological activity and growth that can be reactivated.

label: biological adhesion
description: The attachment of a cell or organism to a substrate, another cell, or other organism. Biological adhesion includes intracellular attachment between membrane regions.

label: organohalogen compound
description: A compound containing at least one carbon-halogen bond.

label: organonitrogen compound
description: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

label: heteroorganic entity
description: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

label: decreased fecundity
description: A fecundity which is relatively low.

label: fecundity
description: A reproductive quality inhering in an organism or population by virtue of the bearer's potential reproductive capacity ad measured by the number of gametes.

label: oxoacid
description: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

label: anatomical structure morphogenesis
description: The process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized. Morphogenesis pertains to the creation of form.

label: occurrent
description: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time. Sometimes also called perdurants.

label: anatomical structure development
description: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an anatomical structure from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure, whatever form that may be including its natural destruction. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

label: cysteine derivative
description: A modified cysteine having either D- or L-configuration.

label: colchicine
description: A carbotricyclic compound comprising 5,6,7,9-tetrahydrobenzo[a]heptalene having four methoxy substituents at the 1-, 2-, 3- and 10-positions as well as an oxo group at the 9-position and an acetamido group at the 7-position.

label: response to chemical
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a chemical stimulus.

label: adult locomotory behavior
description: Locomotory behavior in a fully developed and mature organism.

label: adult behavior
description: Behavior in a fully developed and mature organism.

label: locomotory behavior
description: The specific movement from place to place of an organism in response to external or internal stimuli. Locomotion of a whole organism in a manner dependent upon some combination of that organism's internal state and external conditions.

label: hydroxides
description: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

label: chalcogen molecular entity
description: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

label: polycyclic arene
description: A polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon.

label: ortho- and peri-fused compound
description: A polycyclic compound in which one ring contains two, and only two, atoms in common with each of two or more rings of a contiguous series of rings. Such compounds have n common faces and less than 2n common atoms.

label: thioxanthenes
description: Thioxanthene and its substitution derivatives.

label: organic heterotricyclic compound
description: An organic tricyclic compound in which at least one of the rings of the tricyclic skeleton contains one or more heteroatoms.

label: adult stage
description: The stage of the Drosophila life-cycle from eclosion to death.

label: organonitrogen heterocyclic compound
description: Any organonitrogen compound containing a cyclic component with nitrogen and at least one other element as ring member atoms.

label: p-block molecular entity
description: A p-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a p-block element.

label: hydrocarbon
description: A compound consisting of carbon and hydrogen only.

label: organic fundamental parent
description: An organic fundamental parent is a structure used as a basis for substitutive names in organic nomenclature, containing, in addition to one or more hydrogen atoms, a single atom of an element, a number of atoms (alike or different) linked together to form an unbranched chain, a monocyclic or polycyclic ring system, or a ring assembly or ring/chain system.

label: sulfuric ester
description: An ester of an alcohol and sulfuric acid.

label: ester
description: A compound formally derived from an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l > 0) and an alcohol, phenol, heteroarenol, or enol by linking with formal loss of water from an acidic hydroxy group of the former and a hydroxy group of the latter.

label: adult stage A1
description: Newly eclosed adult stage. Animal free of pupal case. Runs rapidly to find site for wing expansion. Wings are folded back and black against a very pale abdomen.

label: developmental stage
description: A temporal subdivision of a developmental process.

label: adult stage A2
description: Stage, shortly after eclosion, during which the wings expand. During wing expansion, the abdomen pulsates and the hind legs stroke the wings vigorously for several minutes at a time. The stage ends when the wings are folded down over the abdomen, which has become broader and shorter, and the wing cuticle has lost its folds.  The stage lasts around 15 minutes at 25'C.

label: immature adult stage
description: The developmental stage that lasts from eclosion of the adult from the pupal case until tanning is complete (the end of adult stage A3).

label: adult stage A3
description: Adult stage immediately after wing expansion, during which tanning of the cuticle is completed.  This stage lasts approximately 45 minutes at 25'C.

label: nitrogen compound metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic or inorganic compounds that contain nitrogen.

label: cellular metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: carbocyclic compound
description: A cyclic compound in which all of the ring members are carbon atoms.

label: homocyclic compound
description: A cyclic compound having as ring members atoms of the same element only.

label: nucleic acid metabolic process
description: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleic acids.

label: macromolecule metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: cell cycle
description: The progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events. Canonically, the cell cycle comprises the replication and segregation of genetic material followed by the division of the cell, but in endocycles or syncytial cells nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division.

label: single-organism cellular process
description: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, occurring within a single organism.

label: sulfates
description: Salts and esters of sulfuric acid

label: ketone
description: A compound in which a carbonyl group is bonded to two carbon atoms: R2C=O (neither R may be H).

label: sulfide
description: Any sulfur molecular entity that involves either covalently bonded or anionic sulfur.

label: sulfurous acid
description: A sulfur oxoacid that has formula H2O3S.

label: high salt chromatin extraction
description: Material that has been selected using a high salt chromatin extraction, typically 600mM.

label: assay material selection
description: The biosample that is enriched for a specific biomolecule type for further processing.

label: DNase
description: Material that has been selected from a sample treated by deoxyribonuclease.

label: low salt chromatin extraction
description: Material that has been selected using a low salt chromatin extraction, typically 80mM.

label: CAGE
description: Material that has been selected using Cap Analysis Gene Expression, in which the 7-methylguanosine cap at 5' transcript ends is biotinylated and affinity purified.

label: MNase
description: Chromatin that has been cleaved using micrococcal nuclease to cleave at linker DNA between nucleosomes.

label: DamID
description: Material that has been selected using DNA Adenine Methyltransferase Identification, or DamID.

label: FAIRE
description: Material that has been selected using formaldehyde-assisted isolation of Regulatory Elements or FAIRE.

label: assay attribute
description: Some characteristic of an assay pertaining to the methods involved in processing the biological source material or generating the raw output data of the assay.

label: ChIP
description: Material that has been selected using Chromatin Immunoprecipitation, or ChIP.

label: unbound RNA depletion
description: Material that has undergone the depletion of unbound RNA.

label: assay material depletion
description: The biosample that is depleted of specific biomolecule types before further processing.

label: boric acid
description: A member of the boric acids that has formula BH3O3.

label: carboxylic acid anion
description: The conjugate base formed when the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid is deprotonated.

label: oxoanion
description: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.

label: anatomical entity
description: Anatomical entity which is part_of Drosophila melanogaster.

label: p-block element atom
description: Any main group element atom belonging to the p-block of the periodic table.

label: main group element atom
description: An atom belonging to one of the main groups (found in the s- and p- blocks) of the periodic table.

label: ssRNA depletion
description: Material that has undergone the depletion of single-stranded RNA.

label: dsRNA depletion
description: Material that has undergone the depletion of double-stranded RNA.

label: rRNA depletion
description: Material that has undergone the depletion of ribosomal RNA.

label: RNA-protein isolation
description: Isolation of RNA-protein complexes.

label: assay material
description: A type of biomolecule that is isolated from a biosample and characterized by downstream steps in an assay.

label: metabolite isolation
description: Material that is derived from the isolation of metabolites.

label: protein isolation
description: Material that is derived from the isolation of proteins.

label: role
description: A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.

label: chromatin isolation
description: Material that is derived from the isolation of chromatin and its subcellular components and/or binding partners.

label: short RNA isolation
description: The isolation of small RNA species 17-35 nt in size.

label: translated mRNA isolation
description: Material that is derived from the isolation of translated messenger RNA.

label: main group molecular entity
description: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

label: carboxylic acid
description: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

label: carbonyl compound
description: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

label: poly(A) RNA isolation
description: Material that is derived from the isolation of RNA containing a poly(A) tail.

label: quinolines
description: A class of aromatic heterocyclic compounds each of which contains a benzene ring ortho fused to carbons 2 and 3 of a pyridine ring.

label: hycanthone mesylate
description: A methanesulfonate salt resulting from the reaction of equimolar amounts of hycanthone and methanesulfonic acid. It was formerly used as a schistosomicide for individual or mass treatement of infection with Schistosoma haematobium and S. mansoni, but due to its toxicity and concern about possible carcinogenicity, it has been replaced by other drugs such as praziquantel.

label: genomic DNA isolation
description: Material that is derived from isolation of genomic DNA.

label: total RNA isolation
description: Material that is derived from isolation of the total RNA.

label: dataset attribute
description: A descriptor that describes some aspect of a dataset.

label: targeted cell labeling
description: A sample that has been labelled in a targeted, cell-specific manner.

label: biosample method
description: Methods pertaining to the experimental treatment or isolation of a biosample.

label: neuronal activity perturbation
description: Neuronal activity that has been perturbed using genetically controlled agents to activate or depress membrane potential.

label: subcellular fractionation
description: A sample that has undergone fractionation in order to isolate specific subcellular components for study.

label: cell ablation
description: A sample in which specific cells within a tissue have been ablated by some method, such as targeted expression of a cell toxin, or laser ablation of fluorescently marked cells.

label: cell isolation
description: A single cell type that has been isolated by affinity purification or fluorescent cell sorting.

label: N-nitrosodiethylamine
description: A nitrosamine that has formula C4H10N2O.

label: nitrosamine
description: N-Nitroso amines, compounds of the structure R2NNO. Compounds RNHNO are not ordinarily isolable, but they, too, are nitrosamines. The name is a contraction of N-nitrosoamine and, as such, does not require the N locant.

label: entry into diapause
description: The dormancy process that results in entry into diapause. Diapause is a neurohormonally mediated, dynamic state of low metabolic activity. Associated characteristics of this form of dormancy include reduced morphogenesis, increased resistance to environmental extremes, and altered or reduced behavioral activity. Full expression develops in a species-specific manner, usually in response to a number of environmental stimuli that precede unfavorable conditions. Once diapause has begun, metabolic activity is suppressed even if conditions favorable for development prevail. Once initiated, only certain stimuli are capable of releasing the organism from this state, and this characteristic is essential in distinguishing diapause from hibernation.

label: single-organism developmental process
description: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition, involving only one organism.

label: entry into reproductive diapause
description: The dormancy process that results in entry into reproductive diapause. Reproductive diapause is a form of diapause where the organism itself will remain fully active, including feeding and other routine activities, but the reproductive organs experience a tissue-specific reduction in metabolism, with characteristic triggering and releasing stimuli.

label: physical treatment
description: A sample that has been exposed to changes in the physical environment including temperature, pressure and radiation.

label: tissue dissection
description: A sample that has been dissected from the tissue of a more complete organism.

label: biotic treatment
description: Treatment of an organism with a biological stimulus, such as an infectious or parasitic agent.

label: chemical treatment
description: A sample that has been exposed to one or more forms of chemical agent.

label: biosample attribute
description: Characteristics pertaining to the growth conditions, treatments and tissue isolation methods used to generate and obtain a biosample.

label: gene perturbation
description: A sample that has undergone a disruption to the activity of one of its genes.

label: adherent culture
description: The cells that are grown on plates.

label: cell culture property
description: Characteristics pertaining to the cell culture conditions used to generate the biosample.

label: culture supernatant
description: The conditioned medium containing factors secreted by cultured cells that has been isolated.

label: cell cycle synchronized cells
description: A sample that is derived from a population of cells undergoing cell cycle division in a synchronized manner.

label: suspension culture
description: The cells that are grown in liquid culture.

label: response to temperature stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a temperature stimulus.

label: arenesulfonic acid
description: Organic derivatives of sulfonic acid in which the sulfo group is linked directly to carbon of an aryl group.

label: organosulfonic acid
description: An organic derivative of sulfonic acid in which the sulfo group is linked directly to carbon.

label: uncoordinated
description: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: coordination
description: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: organosulfur compound
description: An organosulfur compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-sulfur bond.

label: stationary phase cells
description: A sample that is derived from a population of cells undergoing a stationary phase of division.

label: stably transfected cell line
description: A sample that contains a transfected agent which has been stably incorporated into the genome.

label: log phase cells
description: A sample that is derived from a population of cells undergoing a log phase of division.

label: transiently transfected cell line
description: A sample that contains a transfected agent which is not incorporated into the genome.

label: visual perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception of light stimulus (GO:0050953). 'sensory perception of light stimulus' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0050953'

label: sensory perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception (GO:0007600). 'sensory perception' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007600'

label: abnormal
description: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's deviation from normal or average.

label: sensory perception of light stimulus
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory light stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: light-dark cycle
description: A sample that is maintained in conditions with a specific cycle that included exposure to both light and darkness.

label: growth condition
description: Growth conditions and treatments used to culture the organism prior to biosample isolation.

label: primary cell culture
description: A sample that is derived from a primary cell culture.

label: constant dark
description: A sample that is maintained in conditions comparable to constant darkness.

label: constant light
description: A sample that is maintained in conditions comparable to constant light.

label: virgin
description: A sample in which the individuals have not undergone mating.

label: atrophied
description: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a part or parts of the bearer's being decreased in size due to reduction in tissue mass through wasting.

label: decreased size
description: A size quality which is relatively low.

label: entrainment of circadian clock by photoperiod
description: The synchronization of a circadian rhythm to photoperiod, the intermittent cycle of light (day) and dark (night).

label: altered number of
description: Having extra or fewer parts.

label: has number of
description: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

label: aromatic compound
description: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekule structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

label: thermotaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to a temperature gradient. Movement may be towards either a higher or lower temperature.
synonyms: taxis in response to temperature stimulus

label: taxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to an external stimulus.
synonyms: directed movement in response to stimulus

label: 4-aminofolic acid
description: A dicarboxylic acid that has formula C19H20N8O5.

label: arene
description: Any monocyclic or polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbon.

label: lucanthone
description: A thioxanthen-9-one compound having a methyl substituent at the 1-position and a 2-[(diethylamino)ethyl]amino substituent at the 4-position. Formerly used for the treatment of schistosomiasis. It is a prodrug, being metabolised to hycanthone.

label: N-nitrosodimethylamine
description: A nitrosamine that has formula C2H6N2O.

label: assay method
description: A method used to characterize the biological molecules isolated from a biosample.

label: sulfoxide
description: Compounds having the structure R2S=O (R =/= H).

label: genome representation - partial
description: The assembly represents only part of the organism's genome, because only a single chromosome was targeted, coverage is <1, or total length is less than half the average for other assemblies of the same species.

label: result attribute
description: Some characteristic of a result pertaining to the methods involved in analyzing the input data, or the content or format of the output data.

label: ZFN
description: Sequence change caused by the cleavage of specific DNA sequences by zinc finger nucleases (ZFNs). ZFN proteins comprise a DNA binding domain linked to the DNA cleavage domain of FokI endonuclease. The DNA binding domain is composed of three Cys2His2 zinc fingers, with each zinc finger contacting three consecutive base pairs of DNA. The specificity of the binding is determined by the sequence of the three-zinc finger DNA binding domain, which recognizes a 9 base pair sequence. Cleavage requires dimerization of FokI. The endonuclease is directed to a target region by a pair of ZFNs which bind to sequences in close proximity, allowing dimerization and promoting cleavage.
synonyms: change induced by zinc finger nuclease-mediated cleavage

label: site specific cleavage
description: Sequence change induced by a cleavage event that is caused by an endonuclease that recognizes and cleaves specific sequences in double stranded DNA causing double-strand breaks (DSB).
synonyms: change induced by site specific cleavage

label: assembly level - scaffold
description: Some sequence contigs have been connected across gaps to create scaffolds, but no scaffolds have been placed on chromosomes.

label: genome representation - full
description: The assembly represents the whole genome, though there may still be gaps.

label: cytogenetic mapping
description: Sequences that have been mapped to mitotic or polytene chromosomes to guide genome assembly.

label: assembly level - chromosome
description: There is sequence for one or more chromosomes. This could be a completely sequenced chromosome without gaps or a chromosome containing scaffolds or contigs with gaps between them. There may also be unplaced or unlocalized scaffolds.

label: sequence tagged site mapping
description: Mapping of short (200-500 bp) sequence-tagged sites (STS) landmarks to develop a physical map of a genome.

label: tiling path
description: An ordered list of a minimal set of overlapping clones that provides complete coverage across an assembly.

label: clone-based finishing
description: Sequencing the full extent of selected large clones, typically by sub-cloning large inserts as smaller fragments, to improve the accuracy and completeness of an assembly.

label: restriction fingerprinting
description: Mapping of restriction enzyme recognition sites to develop a physical map of a genome.

label: ortho-fused compound
description: A polycyclic compound in which two rings have two, and only two, atoms in common. Such compounds have n common faces and 2n common atoms.

label: mature adult stage
description: Life stage from the end of adult stage A3, when tanning is complete, to death.

label: bicyclic compound
description: A molecule that features two fused rings.

label: RPM calculation
description: A unit of expression (reads per million reads) in which high-throughput sequencing reads for a given type of feature are normalized against all reads mapping to all features of the same type.

label: RPKM calculation
description: A unit of expression (reads per kilobase per million reads) in which high-throughput sequencing reads mapping to a given feature are normalized both to the size of that feature and to the total number of reads in the sample.

label: RPMM calculation
description: A unit of expression (reads per million miRNA reads) in which high-throughput sequencing reads for a given miRNA are normalized against all reads mapping to all miRNA.

label: uniquely mapping read alignment
description: An alignment of high-throughput sequences that includes only those reads mapping uniquely to the genome.

label: multiply mapping read alignment
description: An alignment of high-throughput sequences that includes reads mapping to multiple sites in the genome. Coverage values for a given sequence weighted equally across the multiple sites to which it maps.

label: conference report
description: The published records of the papers delivered at or issued on the occasion of individual congresses, symposia, and meetings; abstracts of papers delivered at such congresses; reports of the officers and delegates of such congresses; combinations of the foregoing; or proceedings of the conference of a society if they are not limited to matters of internal organization.

label: publication class
description: A publicly available document. It includes individual articles, such as research papers and reviews, and collections of articles, such as scientific journals.

label: stranded profile
description: A genomic mapping profile that distinguishes forward and reverse strand distributions.

label: unstranded profile
description: A genomic mapping profile that does not distinguish between forward and reverse strand mapping.

label: biography
description: A work consisting of an account of the events, works, and achievements, personal and professional, during a person's life. This class includes articles on the activities and accomplishments of living persons as well as the presentation of an obituary.

label: paired-end layout
description: A method that uses an RNA-seq assay in which both ends of the library fragment are sequenced to provide additional mapping constraints.

label: book
description: A publication on a single subject or related subjects that is complete in itself, whether constructed of chapters, sections, or parts, and that is not issued on a regular, ongoing basis. Every chapter is written by the same author or authors of the publication.

label: book review
description: A work consisting of a critical analysis of one or more books or other monographic works.

label: single-end layout
description: A method that uses an RNA-seq assay in which only one end of the library fragment is sequenced.

label: movement of cell or subcellular component
description: The directed, self-propelled movement of a cell or subcellular component without the involvement of an external agent such as a transporter or a pore.

label: abstract
description: An individual abstract of a presentation at a meeting, congress, conference, symposium, colloquium, seminar, workshop, round table, or other professional gathering.

label: autobiography
description: A work consisting of a self-described account.

label: bibliographic list
description: A work consisting of a list of books, articles, documents, publications, and other items, usually on a single subject or related subjects.

label: s-block molecular entity
description: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

label: dimethyl sulfoxide
description: A 2-carbon sulfoxide in which the sulfur atom has two methyl substituents.

label: mass spectrometry
description: A method that uses mass spectrometry, an analytical technique for sorting ions based on mass, for this assay.

label: two channel scanning
description: A method that uses two samples, one a control and the other an experimental sample, for this assay. The samples are labeled in different colors and hybridized to the same oligonucleotide array. Each sample is scanned using different excitation and emission parameters.

label: genomic tiling array
description: A method that uses a genomic tiling array, a subtype of microarray chip in which the genome is represented by oligonucleotides at regularly spaced intervals, for this assay.

label: morphogenesis of a polarized epithelium
description: The morphogenetic process in which the anatomical structures of a polarized epithelium are generated and organized. A polarized epithelium is an epithelium where the epithelial sheet is oriented with respect to the planar axis.

label: morphogenesis of an epithelium
description: The process in which the anatomical structures of epithelia are generated and organized. An epithelium consists of closely packed cells arranged in one or more layers, that covers the outer surfaces of the body or lines any internal cavity or tube.

label: peptide array
description: A method that uses a peptide array, a subtype of microarray chip, for this assay.

label: establishment of planar polarity
description: Coordinated organization of groups of cells in the plane of an epithelium, such that they all orient to similar coordinates.

label: establishment of tissue polarity
description: Coordinated organization of groups of cells in a tissue, such that they all orient to similar coordinates.

label: Affymetrix Gene Expression Array 1
description: A method that uses an Affymetrix Gene Expression Array, version 1, for this assay.

label: Affymetrix Gene Expression Array 2
description: A method that uses an Affymetrix Gene Expression Array, version 2, for this assay.

label: publication descriptor
description: Qualifier that describes the type of publication.

label: descriptor
description: Term that describes an allele, balancer, group or publication.

label: 454 sequencing
description: A method that uses 454 sequencing, a form of high-throughput sequencing with 400-500 nt read length, for this assay.

label: high-throughput sequencing
description: A method that uses high-throughput sequencing for this assay.

label: Illumina sequencing
description: A method that uses Illumina sequencing, a form of high-throughput sequencing, for this assay.

label: single molecule real time sequencing
description: A method that uses single molecule sequencing, by highly processive DNA polymerase to generate an extremely long single read on the order of several kilobases, for this assay.

label: phosphoramide
description: A compound in which one or more of the OH groups of phosphoric acid have been replaced with an amino or substituted amino group. The term is commonly confined to the phosphoric triamides, P(=O)(NR2)3, since replacement of one or two OH groups produces phosphoramidic acids: P(=O)(OH)(NR2)2 , P(=O)(OH)2(NR2).

label: primary amide
description: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label: viable
description: A viability quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer's ability to survive or the long term survival ability of a given population.

label: viability
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer's disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

label: lethal (sensu genetics)
description: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of the bearer's long term survival inability.

label: Sanger sequencing
description: A method that uses Sanger sequencing for this assay.

label: nuclear run-on
description: Nucleotide analogs that are used to map the position and orientation of the RNA polymerase active site.

label: epithelium development
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an epithelium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. An epithelium is a tissue that covers the internal or external surfaces of an anatomical structure.

label: tissue development
description: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a tissue over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: random priming
description: Random oligomers that have been used to prime first strand cDNA synthesis by reverse transcriptase at random positions along transcripts.

label: density sedimentation
description: Material that has been selected based on density via density sedimentation.

label: qualifier
description: Term used to qualify a descriptor.

label: oligo-dT selection
description: Material that has been selected using short sequences of deoxy-thymine nucleotides to affinity purify RNA containing long polyA stretches.

label: oligo-dT priming
description: Material that has been selected using short sequences of deoxy-thymine nucleotides to prime first strand cDNA synthesis by reverse transcriptase at long polyA stretches.

label: affinity purification
description: Material that has been selected using affinity purification.

label: size fractionation
description: Material that has been selected using size fractionation.

label: 7-bromomethyl-12-methyltetraphene
description: A member of the class of tetraphenes that is tetraphene in which the hydrogens at positions 7 and 12 are replaced by bromomethyl and methyl groups, respectively.

label: organobromine compound
description: A compound containing at least one carbon-bromine bond.

label: variable
description: Expression pattern that changes throughout the assayed anatomical entity.

label: morphological qualifier
description: Qualifier that describes an observed expression pattern.

label: mononucleosomal DNA isolation
description: Mononucleosomal fragments, generated by micrococcal nuclease cleavage at linker DNA between nucleosomes, that have been isolated by gel electrophoresis.

label: carbopolycyclic compound
description: A polyclic compound in which all of the ring members are carbon atoms.

label: naphthalenes
description: Any benzenoid aromatic compound having a skeleton composed of two ortho-fused benzene rings.

label: punctate
description: Expression pattern that resembles small dots.

label: methanesulfonates
description: Esters or salts of methanesulfonic acid.

label: uniform
description: Expression pattern that is constant throughout the assayed anatomical entity.

label: intense
description: Strong expression.

label: cell
description: The basic structural and functional unit of all organisms. Includes the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: cellular_component
description: The part of a cell, extracellular environment or virus in which a gene product is located. A gene product may be located in one or more parts of a cell and its location may be as specific as a particular macromolecular complex, that is, a stable, persistent association of macromolecules that function together.

label: immune response
description: Any immune system process that functions in the calibrated response of an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat.

label: immune system process
description: Any process involved in the development or functioning of the immune system, an organismal system for calibrated responses to potential internal or invasive threats.

label: faint
description: Weak expression.

label: granular
description: Expression pattern that resembles small grains or particles.

label: maternal effect
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as showing a maternal effect when the phenotype of an individual is a manifestation of the genotype of the mother, rather than the genotype of the individual.

label: parental effect
description: Parental effects describe the dependence of the expression of a phenotypic attribute of an allele on the parent from which that allele is inherited.

label: non-rescuable maternal effect
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as showing a non-rescuable maternal effect (strict maternal effect) when the introduction of a wild-type copy of the responsible mutation from the father has no ameliorating effect on the maternal effect mutant phenotype.

label: rescuable maternal effect
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as showing a rescuable maternal effect when the introduction of a wild-type copy of the responsible mutation from the father ameliorates the maternal effect mutant phenotype.

label: paternal effect
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as showing a paternal effect when the phenotype of an individual is a manifestation of the genotype of the father, rather than the genotype of the individual.

label: reflex
description: An automatic response to a stimulus beginning with a nerve impulse from a receptor and ending with the action of an effector such as a gland or a muscle. Signaling never reaches a level of consciousness.

label: has fewer parts of type
description: The bearer of this quality has_part < n AND has_part > 0 of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly.

label: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type
description: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.

label: decreased object quality
description: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: has extra parts of type
description: The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.

label: increased object quality
description: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: cell non-autonomous
description: A phenotypic effect which is not expressed in/limited to cells of the mutant genetic constitution under investigation is said to be cell non-autonomous.

label: cell autonomy qualifier
description: Cell autonomy statements describe the cellular focus of mutant phenotype, generally revealed by genetic mosaic analysis, in terms of whether the mutant has its phenotypic effect limited to, or not limited to, cells of the mutant genotype.

label: single balancer
description: Chromosome that carries inversions and visible mutations, and which can be used to identify the genotype of an individual.

label: balancer descriptor
description: Descriptor that relates to aspects of a balancer.

label: cold sensitive amorphic allele
description: An allele that completely lacks function (i.e. whose gene productive is completely inactive) at low temperatures, but that retains at least some function at higher temperatures.

label: temperature conditional amorphic allele
description: An allele that completely lacks function (i.e. whose gene productive is completely inactive) at some temperatures, but not others.

label: cold sensitive loss of function allele
description: An allele that at low temperatures but not high temperatures, either makes no functional gene product, makes reduced levels of a normally functioning gene product or makes a gene product with reduced activity compared to wild-type.

label: cold sensitive
description: Phenotype only expressed at low temperatures.

label: segmentally repeated
description: Restricted to a segmentally repeated pattern with some specified type.

label: spatial qualifier
description: Qualifier that describes the spatial characteristics of a phenotype or expression pattern.

label: cell autonomous
description: A phenotypic effect which is expressed in and limited to cells of the mutant genetic constitution under investigation is said to be cell autonomous.

label: response to osmotic stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of solutes outside the organism or cell.

label: neoplastic
description: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter's disposition the presence of abnormally proliferating masses of cells.

label: structure
description: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

label: even pair rule expression pattern
description: Expression in even, but not odd numbered segment of the blastoderm.

label: pair rule expression pattern
description: Expression in alternate segments of the blastoderm.

label: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating damage to its DNA from environmental insults or errors during metabolism.

label: cellular response to stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: odd pair rule expression pattern
description: Expression in odd, but not even numbered segments of the blastoderm.

label: species list
description: A list of species found in a specified area.

label: dorsal ventral gradient
description: Expression pattern which varies in intensity following a gradient in the dorsal-ventral axis.

label: gradient
description: Expression pattern which varies in intensity following a gradient in a specific axis.

label: striped
description: Restricted to stripes in some specified type.

label: I-CreI
description: Sequence change caused by the cleavage of a 19-24 bp palindromic DNA site by the I-CreI endonuclease.
synonyms: change induced by I-CreI endonuclease cleavage

label: response to oxidative stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.

label: FlyBase analysis
description: A record of an analysis carried out by FlyBase that has not been formally published.

label: unpublished
description: A work that has not been formally published.

label: hydrides
description: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.

label: anterior posterior gradient
description: Expression pattern which varies in intensity following a gradient in the anterior-posterior axis.

label: bromohydrocarbon
description: A compound derived from a hydrocarbon by replacing a hydrogen atom with a bromine atom.

label: halohydrocarbon
description: A compound derived from a hydrocarbon by replacing a hydrogen atom with a halogen atom.

label: haloalkane
description: A compound derived from an alkane by replacing a hydrogen atom with a halogen atom.

label: actinomycin
description: A large group of antibiotics isolated from various species of Streptomyces and characterised by having a substituted phenoxazine ring linked to two cyclic heterodetic peptides.

label: quinhydrone
description: An addition compound that has formula C12H10O4.

label: addition compound
description: An addition compound contains two or more simpler compounds that can be packed in a definite ratio into a crystal. The term covers donor-acceptor complexes (adducts) and a variety of lattice compounds.

label: 80-90% egg length
description: 80-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: egg length
description: Position in the egg or pre-gastrula embryo expressed as a percentage of egg length, where 0% corresponds to the posterior tip and 100% to the anterior tip.

label: 90% egg length
description: 90% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 90-100% egg length
description: 90-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 70-100% egg length
description: 70-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 70-80% egg length
description: 70-80% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 70-90% egg length
description: 70-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 80% egg length
description: 80% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 60-90% egg length
description: 60-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 70% egg length
description: 70% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 60-80% egg length
description: 60-80% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50-80% egg length
description: 50-80% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50-90% egg length
description: 50-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 60% egg length
description: 60% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 60-100% egg length
description: 60-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50% egg length
description: 50% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50-100% egg length
description: 50-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50-60% egg length
description: 50-60% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 50-70% egg length
description: 50-70% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-90% egg length
description: 40-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-70% egg length
description: 40-70% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-80% egg length
description: 40-80% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40% egg length
description: 40% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-100% egg length
description: 40-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-50% egg length
description: 40-50% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 40-60% egg length
description: 40-60% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 30-60% egg length
description: 30-60% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: p-N,N-di(2-chloroethyl)aminophenylvaleric acid
synonyms: mutation induced by p-N,N-di(2-chloroethyl)aminophenylvaleric acid exposure

label: 30-70% egg length
description: 30-70% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: phenylpropanoid
description: Any organic aromatic compound with a structure based on a phenylpropane skeleton. The class includes naturally occurring phenylpropanoid esters, flavonoids, anthocyanins, coumarins and many small phenolic molecules as well as their semi-synthetic and synthetic analogs. Phenylpropanoids are also precursors of lignin.
