description: A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in membrane-bounded vesicles; transported substances are enclosed in the vesicle lumen or located in the vesicle membrane. The process begins with a step that directs a substance to the forming vesicle, and includes vesicle budding and coating. Vesicles are then targeted to, and fuse with, an acceptor membrane.

label: secretion by cell
description: The controlled release of a substance by a cell.

label: white paper
description: A work consisting of a set of statements, directions, or principles presenting current or future rules or policy.

label: thesis
description: A work consisting of a formal presentation made usually to fulfill requirements for an academic degree.

label: curated genome annotation
description: A systematic effort to annotate gene models on a sequenced Drosophila genome, such as those conducted for D. melanogaster at the Celera Jamboree. Annotations may be performed manually or automatically.

label: supplementary material
description: Supporting content or information, such as animation, datasets, multimedia files, video, movies, audio files, text files, or software, which is submitted for publication in an online journal or an online edition of a journal. This information may be referenced in the text of the article with a link to the supplementary data provided.

label: endocytosis
description: A vesicle-mediated transport process in which cells take up external materials or membrane constituents by the invagination of a small region of the plasma membrane to form a new membrane-bounded vesicle.

label: teaching note
description: An article describing exercises or practicals suitable for teaching.

label: review
description: An article or book published after examination of published material on a subject.

label: spoof
description: A mildly satirical mockery or parody of a conventional publication type.

label: stock list
description: A list of Drosophila stocks kept by a specified stock center or research group.

label: response to pain
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a pain stimulus. Pain stimuli cause activation of nociceptors, peripheral receptors for pain, include receptors which are sensitive to painful mechanical stimuli, extreme heat or cold, and chemical stimuli.

label: multicellular organismal response to stress
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a multicellular organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: press release
description: A written or recorded communication directed at members of the news media for the purpose of announcing something ostensibly newsworthy.

label: retraction
description: A work consisting of a statement issued by one or more authors of an article or a book, withdrawing or disavowing acknowledgement of their participation in performing research or writing the results of their study.

label: patent
description: A work consisting of documents granted by a government giving exclusive rights to an inventor or assignee to manufacture, use, or sell an invention for a certain number of years.

label: embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype
description: A phenotype that is a disruption in the wild-type pattern of segments or parasegments of the embryo or larva.

label: personal communication to FlyBase
description: A work that has not been formally published and that consists of observations or data submitted by a researcher or group of researchers directly to FlyBase.

label: pair rule phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype that is the complete or partial loss of alternate segments or parasegments.

label: poem
description: A literary or oral work expressing meaning via symbolism and following formal or informal patterns.

label: actinomycin D
description: An actinomycin that has formula C62H86N12O16.

label: poster
description: A work consisting of a single or multi-sheet notice made to attract attention to events, activities, causes, goods, or services. It is for posting, usually in a public place and is chiefly pictorial. It is intended to make an immediate impression from a distance.

label: hypermorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: Allele shown by molecular evidence to make either a functionally wild-type gene product at increased levels or a gene product with the same function as wild-type but with increased activity.

label: antimorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele that has been shown by molecular evidence to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product.

label: note
description: A work consisting of a critical or explanatory note written to discuss, support, or dispute an article or other presentation previously published.

label: obituary
description: A published announcement of a death accompanied by a short biography of the deceased.

label: paper
description: An article reporting original research, published in a peer-reviewed journal.

label: hypomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity.

label: neomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to produce a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type.

label: diazines
description: Any organic heterocyclic compound containing a benzene ring in which two of the C-H fragments have been replaced by isolobal nitrogens (the diazine parent structure).

label: letter
description: A work consisting of written or printed communication between individuals or between persons and representatives of corporate bodies. The correspondence may be personal or professional.

label: news article
description: A work consisting of an announcement or statement of recent or current events of new data and matters of interest in the field of medicine or science, published in a scientific journal.

label: protein sequence record
description: A record of a protein sequence in some standard format, such as UniProtKB.

label: sequence record
description: A record of a nucleotide or protein sequence in some standard format.

label: axis specification defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in axis specification (GO:0009798). 'axis specification' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0009798'

label: erratum
description: A work consisting of an acknowledgement of an error, issued by a publisher, editor, or author.

label: film
description: A film or video that is factual, documentary or instructional in character.

label: amorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to completely lack function, producing either a completely inactive gene product or none at all.

label: interview
description: A work consisting of a conversation with an individual regarding his or her background and other personal and professional details, opinions on specific subjects posed by the interviewer.

label: touch perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception of touch (GO:0050975). 'sensory perception of touch' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0050975'

label: temperature response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to temperature stimulus (GO:0009266). 'response to temperature stimulus' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0009266'

label: cold stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to cold (GO:0009409). 'response to cold' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0009409'

label: stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to stress (GO:0006950). 'response to stress' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006950'

label: response to cold
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cold stimulus, a temperature stimulus below the optimal temperature for that organism.

label: phenotype qualifier
description: Qualifier that describes an observable phenotype.

label: DNA/RNA sequence record
description: A record of a DNA or RNA sequence in some standard format, such as GenBank or EMBL or DDBJ.

label: proboscis extension reflex defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in proboscis extension reflex (GO:0007637). 'proboscis extension reflex' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007637'

label: chemosensitive behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in chemosensory behavior (GO:0007635). 'chemosensory behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007635'.'

label: proboscis extension reflex
description: The extension, through direct muscle actions, of the proboscis (the trunk-like extension of the mouthparts on the adult external head) in response to a sugar stimulus.
synonyms: behavioral response to sugar stimulus, proboscis extension

label: quinone
description: Compounds having a fully conjugated cyclic dione structure, such as that of benzoquinones, derived from aromatic compounds by conversion of an even number of -CH= groups into -C(=O)- groups with any necessary rearrangement of double bonds (polycyclic and heterocyclic analogues are included).

label: dibenz[a,h]anthracene
description: An ortho-fused polycyclic arene that has formula C22H14.

label: compound sense organ
description: Any compound cell cluster organ (FBbt:00007230) that functions in (some) detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050906).

label: compound cell cluster organ
description: An anatomical structure consisting of multiple cell cluster organs and which does not contain portions of tissue.

label: homeotic
description: Phenotype that is the partial or full transformation of one or more segments (FBbt:00000003) or segmental appendages from one identity to another. For example, in antennapedia an antenna is partially or fully transformed into a leg.

label: sleep
description: Any process in which an organism enters and maintains a periodic, readily reversible state of reduced awareness and metabolic activity. Usually accompanied by physical relaxation, the onset of sleep in humans and other mammals is marked by a change in the electrical activity of the brain.

label: gap expression pattern
description: Expression across a contiguous block of two or more segments of the blastoderm.

label: temperature conditional
description: Phenotype only expressed in some subset of the temperature range within which wild-type animals are viable.

label: drug conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only in the presence of some specific drug (CHEBI:23888) whose presence does not induce the same defect in wild-type animals.

label: chemical conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only in the presence or absence of some specific chemical whose presence or absence does not induce the same defect in wild-type animals.

label: RU486 conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only in the presence of RU486 (CHEBI:50692), also known as mifepristone.

label: tetracycline conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only in the presence of tetracycline (CHEBI:27902).

label: premature aging
description: A phenotype in which the aging process (GO:0007568) is accelerated compared to wild-type.

label: aging defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in aging (GO:0007568). 'aging' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007568'

label: aging
description: A developmental process that is a deterioration and loss of function over time. Aging includes loss of functions such as resistance to disease, homeostasis, and fertility, as well as wear and tear. Aging includes cellular senescence, but is more inclusive. May precede death and may succeed developmental maturation (GO:0021700).

label: progressive
description: An adult phenotype that becomes more severe with age.

label: conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only under specific environmental conditions that do not induce the same defect in wild-type animals.

label: heat sensitive
description: Phenotype only expressed at high temperatures.

label: database
description: Work consisting of a structured file of information or a set of logically related data stored and retrieved using computer-based means.

label: delayed aging
description: A phenotype in which the aging process (GO:0007568) is slower than in wild-type.

label: cell
description: Anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

label: increased size
description: A size quality which is relatively high.

label: size
description: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

label: reproductive quality
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to produce new life or offspring.

label: organismal quality
description: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

label: flavans
description: Any flavonoid with a 3,4-dihydro-2-aryl-2H-1-benzopyran skeleton and its substituted derivatives.

label: sex limited
description: Expression is limited to one or other sex by virtue of the particular biology of that sex, rather than the sex-linkage of the genes underlying the attribute.

label: sex
description: Qualifier that relates the expression of a phenotype to the sex of the individual.

label: male limited
description: Expression is limited to males by virtue of the particular biology of males, rather than the sex-linkage of the gene(s) involved.

label: female limited
description: Expression is limited to females by virtue of the particular biology of females, rather than the sex-linkage of the gene(s) involved.

label: cold sensitive hypermorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a functionally wild-type gene product at increased levels or with increased activity where this increased expression or activity occurs at low temperatures but not higher temperatures.

label: cold sensitive hypermorphic allele
description: An allele that, at low temperatures but not higher temperatures, makes a gene product with normal function but at higher levels or with higher activity than in wild-type..

label: temperature conditional hypermorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a functionally wild-type gene product at increased levels or with increased activity where this increased expression or activity occurs at some temperatures but not others.

label: semidominant
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as semidominant when individuals heterozygous for the allele show phenotypes part way between homozygotes for either allele.

label: heat sensitive hypermorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a functionally wild-type gene product at increased levels or with increased activity where this increased expression or activity occurs at high temperatures but not lower temperatures.

label: heat sensitive hypermorphic allele
description: An allele that, at high temperatures but not lower temperatures, makes a gene product with normal function but at higher levels or with higher activity than in wild-type.

label: journal
description: A publication issued on a regular, ongoing basis containing separate research articles and other writings such as reviews, comments and conference reports.

label: newspaper article
description: A work consisting of a news item appearing in a general-interest newspaper or other general news periodical, containing information of current and timely interest in the field of medicine or science.

label: temperature conditional hypermorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to make a normal gene product at increased levels or with increased activity compared to wild-type, where this increased amount or activity is present at some temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not others (permissive temperatures), and where the genetic evidence consists of the observation that extra copies in the genome increase the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at the non-permissive temperatures.

label: temperature conditional hypermorphic allele
description: An allele that, at some temperatures but not others, makes a gene product with normal function but at higher levels or with higher activity than in wild-type.

label: cold sensitive hypermorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to make a normal gene product at increased levels or with increased activity compared to wild-type, where this increased amount or activity is present at low temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not higher temperatures (permissive temperatures), and where the genetic evidence consists of the observation that extra copies in the genome increase the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at the non-permissive temperatures.

label: amino acid
description: A carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups.

label: heat sensitive hypermorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to make a normal gene product at increased levels or with increased activity compared to wild-type, where this increased amount or activity is present at high temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not lower temperatures (permissive temperatures), and where the genetic evidence consists of the observation that extra copies in the genome increase the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at the non-permissive temperatures.

label: codominant
description: A phenotypic attribute is described as codominant when it is manifest in individuals carrying the allele that causes that phenotype, irrespective of the homologous allele.

label: cold sensitive gain of function allele
description: An allele that at low temperatures but not high temperatures, either makes a normally functioning gene product but at higher levels or in a different spatial or temporal pattern to wild-type, or a product with increased or novel activity compared to wild-type.

label: morphology
description: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

label: biological sex
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

label: temperature conditional gain of function allele
description: An allele that at some temperatures but not others, either makes a normally functioning gene product but at higher levels or in a different spatial or temporal pattern to wild-type, or a product with increased or novel activity compared to wild-type.

label: chlorambucil
description: A nitrogen mustard that has formula C14H19Cl2NO2.

label: heat sensitive gain of function allele
description: An allele that at high temperatures but not low temperatures, either makes a normally functioning gene product but at higher levels or in a different spatial or temporal pattern to wild-type, or a product with increased or novel activity compared to wild-type.

label: heat sensitive neomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele that, is inferred to make a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type at some high temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not lower temperatures (permissive temperatures), based on the evidence that the phenotype at the non-permissive temperature is unaffected by extra or fewer doses of the wild-type gene.

label: heat sensitive neomorphic allele
description: An allele that, at some high temperatures but not lower temperatures, makes a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type.

label: temperature conditional neomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele that, is inferred to make a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type at some temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not others (permissive temperatures) based on the evidence that the phenotype at the non-permissive temperature is unaffected by extra or fewer doses of the wild-type gene.

label: temperature conditional neomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to produce a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern (compared to wild-type) at some temperatures but not others.

label: temperature conditional neomorphic allele
description: An allele that, at some temperatures but not others, makes a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type.

label: cold sensitive neomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to produce a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern (compared to wild-type) at low temperatures but not higher temperatures.

label: cold sensitive neomorphic allele
description: An allele that, at some low temperatures but not higher temperatures, makes a gene product at with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type.

label: heat sensitive neomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to produce a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern (compared to wild-type) at high temperatures but not lower temperatures.

label: mitomycin C
description: A mitomycin that has formula C15H18N4O5.

label: cold sensitive neomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele that, is inferred to make a gene product with a novel function or expression pattern compared to wild-type at some low temperatures (non-permissive temperatures) but not higher temperatures (permissive temperatures), based on the evidence that the phenotype at the non-permissive temperature is unaffected by extra or fewer doses of the wild-type gene.

label: cold sensitive antimorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele that has been shown by molecular evidence to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at low temperatures but not higher temperatures.

label: temperature conditional antimorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele that has been shown by molecular evidence to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at some temperatures but not others.

label: cold sensitive antimorphic allele
description: An allele that makes a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at cold temperatures, but not at higher temperatures.

label: heat sensitive antimorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele that has been shown by molecular evidence to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at high temperatures but not lower temperatures.

label: heat sensitive antimorphic allele
description: An allele that makes a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at high temperatures, but not at lower temperatures.

label: temperature conditional antimorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the wild-type gene product at some temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at others (permissive temperatures) from the observation that, at the non-permissive temperatures, the phenotype over a deficiency is stronger than that over a wild-type allele, which in turn is stronger than that in the presence of a duplication of the wild-type locus.

label: temperature conditional antimorphic allele
description: An allele that makes a gene product that is antagonistic to the function of the wild-type gene product at some temperatures, but not others.

label: cold sensitive antimorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the wild-type gene product at low temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at high temperatures (permissive temperatures) from the observation that, at the non-permissive temperatures, the phenotype over a deficiency is stronger than that over a wild-type allele, which in turn is stronger than that in the presence of a duplication of the wild-type locus.

label: heat sensitive antimorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to make a gene product that is antagonistic to the wild-type gene product at high temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at lower temperatures (permissive temperatures) from the observation that, at the non-permissive temperatures, the phenotype over a deficiency is stronger than that over a wild-type allele, which in turn is stronger than that in the presence of a duplication of the wild-type locus.

label: temporal distribution quality
description: A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.

label: heat sensitive hypomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to have normal activity at low temperatures (permissive temperatures) but to make a gene product with normal function but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity at higher temperatures (non-permissive temperatures). The genetic evidence must consist of an observation extra copies in the genome decrease the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at non-permissive temperatures. Most commonly this evidence takes the form of experiments showing that the homozygote (2 copies) has a weaker phenotype at non-permissive temperatures than the allele in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy)).

label: heat sensitive hypomorphic allele
description: An allele that makes a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but which at high temperatures is present in a lesser amount or with lowered activity, and that retains normal levels of expression or activity at low temperatures.

label: temperature conditional hypomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to have normal activity at some temperatures (permissive temperatures) but at other temperatures to make a gene product with normal function but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity (non-permissive temperatures). The genetic evidence must consist of an observation extra copies in the genome decrease the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at non-permissive temperatures. Most commonly this evidence takes the form of experiments showing that the homozygote (2 copies) has a weaker phenotype at non-permissive temperatures than the allele in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy)).

label: temperature conditional hypomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a normal gene product in normal amounts at some temperatures, but at other temperatures to make a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity.

label: temperature conditional hypomorphic allele
description: An allele that, at some temperatures but not others, makes a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity.

label: cold sensitive hypomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a normal gene product in normal amounts at high temperatures, but at lower temperatures to make a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity.

label: cold sensitive hypomorphic allele
description: An allele that makes a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but which at low temperatures is present in a lesser amount or with lowered activity, and that retains normal function at higher temperatures.

label: heat sensitive hypomorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to make a normal gene product in normal amounts at low temperatures, but at higher temperatures to make a gene product that is functionally equivalent to wild-type but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity.

label: heat sensitive loss of function allele
description: An allele that at high temperatures but not low temperatures, either makes no functional gene product, makes reduced levels of a normally functioning gene product or makes a gene product with reduced activity compared to wild-type.

label: cold sensitive hypomorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred from genetic evidence to have normal activity at high temperatures (permissive temperatures) but to make a gene product with normal function but in a lesser amount or with lowered activity at lower temperatures (non-permissive temperatures). The genetic evidence must consist of an observation extra copies in the genome decrease the expressivity and/or penetrance of the phenotype at non-permissive temperatures. Most commonly this evidence takes the form of experiments showing that the homozygote (2 copies) has a weaker phenotype at non-permissive temperatures than the allele in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy)).

label: temperature conditional loss of function allele
description: An allele that at some temperatures but not others either makes no functional gene product or makes reduced levels of a normally functioning gene product or makes a gene product with reduced activity compared to wild-type.

label: chlorohydrocarbon
description: A compound derived from a hydrocarbon by replacing a hydrogen atom with a chlorine atom.

label: heat sensitive amorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to completely lack function at high temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at low temperatures (permissive temperatures) from the observation that adding extra copies in the genome has no effect on the phenotype at the restrictive temperatures. Most commonly, evidence takes the form of the observation that the phenotype of homozygotes (2 copies) is identical to that seen when the allele is in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy).

label: heat sensitive amorphic allele
description: An allele that completely lacks function (i.e. whose gene productive is completely inactive) at high temperatures, but that retains at least some function at lower temperatures.

label: temperature conditional amorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to completely lack function at some temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not others (permissive temperatures) from the observation that addition of extra copies in the genome has no effect on the phenotype at the restrictive temperatures. Most commonly, evidence takes the form of the observation that the phenotype of homozygotes (2 copies) is identical to that seen when the allele is in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy).

label: cold sensitive amorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to completely lack function at low temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at high temperatures (permissive temperatures).

label: temperature conditional amorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to completely lack function at some temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at others (permissive temperatures).

label: heat sensitive amorphic allele - molecular evidence
description: An allele shown by molecular evidence to completely lack function at high temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at low temperatures (permissive temperatures).

label: response to heat
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a heat stimulus, a temperature stimulus above the optimal temperature for that organism.

label: cold sensitive amorphic allele - genetic evidence
description: An allele inferred to completely lack function at low temperatures (restrictive temperatures) but not at high temperatures (permissive temperatures) from the observation that adding extra copies in the genome has no effect on the phenotype at the restrictive temperatures. Most commonly, evidence takes the form of the observation that the phenotype of homozygotes (2 copies) is identical to that seen when the allele is in trans to a deletion of the gene (1 copy).

label: increased quality
description: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: edited book
description: A publication that is not issued on a regular, ongoing basis containing separate articles or chapters (typically reviews) written by different authors on a single subject or related subjects, overseen by one or more editors.

label: decreased quality
description: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: terminal phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype that is the complete or partial loss of terminal regions of the embryo/larva: the acron, telson and immediately adjacent segments.

label: virgin female limited
description: Expression is limited to virgin females.

label: mated female limited
description: Expression is limited to mated females.

label: mated male limited
description: Expression is limited to mated males.

label: response to radiation
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an electromagnetic radiation stimulus. Electromagnetic radiation is a propagating wave in space with electric and magnetic components. These components oscillate at right angles to each other and to the direction of propagation.

label: virgin male limited
description: Expression is limited to virgin males.

label: sensitivity of a process
description: A quality of a process inhering in bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to respond to stimulation.

label: formaldehyde
description: The simplest aldehyde.

label: mated female
description: Expressed in mated females.

label: female
description: Expressed in females.

label: virgin male
description: Expressed in virgin males.

label: male
description: Expressed in males.

label: mated male
description: Expressed in mated males.

label: neoplasia
description: Phenotype that consists of abnormal growth of a tissue or organ due to increased numbers of cells, but in which the affected tissue or organ does not maintain its normal form.

label: increased cell number
description: Phenotype that is an increase in the number of cells in a whole animal or in some specific organ, tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: hypoplasia
description: Phenotype that is a reduction in size of an organ or tissue compared to wild-type due to reduced numbers of cells being produced during its development or growth.

label: hypoplastic
description: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced number of cells within an organ or tissue.

label: decreased cell number
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in the number of cells in a whole animal or in some specific organ, tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type. This phenotype is not necessarily accompanied by decreased growth - there may be fewer cells in an otherwise normal volume of tissue.

label: oxidative stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to oxidative stress (GO:0006979). 'response to oxidative stress' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006979'

label: virgin female
description: Expressed in virgin females.

label: jump response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect or in or absence of a jump response (GO:0007630). The jump response in Drosophila is a reflex escape response that can be triggered by a number of signals including odor and light. Standard assays are commonly used to test odor and light induced jump response.

label: jumping defective
description: Phenotype that is a reduced ability to jump or a reduced jump response. This may be due to neurological or muscular defects.

label: locomotor behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in locomotory behavior (GO:0007626). 'locomotory behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007626'

label: jump response
description: The sudden, usually upward, movement off the ground or other surface through sudden muscular effort in the legs, following exposure to an external stimulus.

label: mating behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in mating behavior (GO:0007617). 'mating behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007617'

label: mating defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in mating (GO:0007618). 'mating' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007618'

label: somatic clone - Minute background
description: A clone of somatic cells that share a mutant genotype that includes being Minute +/+ and that is part of and derived from an animal with a different genotype that includes being Minute +/-.

label: somatic clone
description: A clone of somatic cells that share a genotype that is different from the genotype of the animal in which it resides and from which it is derived.

label: regulation of metabolic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: regulation of biological process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: polynucleotide
description: A nucleobase-containing molecular entity with an oligomeric structure comprised of a linear sequence of 13 or more nucleotide residues.

label: cell migration defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in cell migration (GO:0016477). 'cell migration' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0016477'

label: cell migration
description: The controlled self-propelled movement of a cell from one site to a destination guided by molecular cues. Cell migration is a central process in the development and maintenance of multicellular organisms.

label: increased cell growth
description: Phenotype that is an increase in the rate of cell growth (GO:0016049) in a whole animal or in some specific organ tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: cell growth defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in cell growth (GO:0016049). 'cell growth' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0016049'

label: cell growth
description: The process in which a cell irreversibly increases in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

label: decreased cell growth
description: Phenotype that is an decrease in the rate of cell growth (GO:0016049) in a whole animal or in some specific organ tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: atrophy
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in size of an initially normally sized organ or tissue due to wasting away of cells.

label: ends-in gene targeting
description: Change of a genomic sequence via homologous recombinational repair (GO:0000724) that is induced by a double strand break within an engineered homologous donor sequence. This typically generates a tandem duplication of the homologous sequence from the donor, separated by the remainder of the incoming donor DNA. However, more complicated outcomes are possible.
synonyms: change induced by ends-in gene targeting

label: gene targeting by homologous recombination
description: Change of a genomic sequence via homologous recombinational repair (GO:0000724) that is induced by a double stranded break in an engineered donor construct that contains sequence homologous to the target gene.
synonyms: change induced by gene targeting via homologous recombination

label: jumpless
description: Phenotype that is a inability to jump. This may be due to neurological or muscular defects.

label: nutrition conditional
description: Phenotype only expressed under some specific nutritional regime.

label: calorie restriction conditional
description: Phenotype only expressed under conditions where calorie intake is restricted.

label: recombination
description: Sequence change induced by the genetic exchange that takes place between DNA sequences.

label: oxide
description: An oxide is a chemical compound of oxygen with other chemical elements.

label: ends-out gene targeting
description: Change of a genomic sequence via homologous recombinational repair (GO:0000724) that is induced by a double strand break on both sides of the homologous region in an engineered donor sequence. This double-strand break is usually generated by cutting at a single site adjacent to the homologous region in a circularized donor sequence. This typically generates a simple targeted replacement of the target sequence by the donor sequence. However, more complicated outcomes are possible.
synonyms: change induced by ends-out gene targeting

label: cell cycle process
description: The cellular process that ensures successive accurate and complete genome replication and chromosome segregation.

label: cell number defective
description: Phenotype that is an increase or decrease in the number of cells in a whole animal or in some specific organ, tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type. This phenotype is not necessarily accompanied by defects in cell growth - there may be a greater or lesser number of cells in an otherwise normal volume of tissue.

label: sleep defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sleep (GO:0030431). 'sleep' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0030431'

label: diapause defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in entry into diapause (GO:0055115). 'entry into diapause' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0055115'

label: reproductive diapause defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in entry into reproductive diapause (GO:0055116). 'entry into reproductive diapause' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0055116'

label: starvation stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to starvation (GO:0042594). 'response to starvation' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0042594'

label: odd pair-rule phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype that is the complete or partial loss of odd segments.

label: segment polarity phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype in which some fraction of each segment (along the anterior-posterior axis) is deleted and replaced by a mirror image duplication of the remaining part of the segment.

label: gap phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype that is the complete loss of a contiguous stretch of 2 or more segments.

label: reproduction
description: The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.

label: even pair-rule phenotype
description: Embryonic/larval segmentation phenotype that is the complete or partial loss of even segments.

label: decreased occurrence of cell division
description: A phenotype that is a decreased occurrence of cell division (GO:0051301). 'cell division' is defined as '$sub_GO:0051301'.

label: cell division
description: The process resulting in division and partitioning of components of a cell to form more cells; may or may not be accompanied by the physical separation of a cell into distinct, individually membrane-bounded daughter cells.

label: increased occurrence of cell division
description: A phenotype that is an increased occurrence of cell division (GO:0051301). 'cell division' is defined as '$sub_GO:0051301'.

label: oviposition defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in oviposition (GO:0007620). 'oviposition' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0018991'.

label: decreased fecundity
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in the number of gametes produced.

label: increased fecundity
description: Phenotype that is an increase in the number of gametes produced.

label: increased fecundity
description: A fecundity which is relatively high

label: copulation defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in copulation (GO:0007620). 'copulation' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007620'

label: copulation
description: The act of sexual union between male and female, involving the transfer of sperm.

label: energy taxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to physical parameters involved in energy generation, such as light, oxygen, and oxidizable substrates.

label: ion
description: A molecular entity having a net electric charge.

label: cellular response to stimulus
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus by a cell and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell.

label: glycoside
description: A glycosyl compound resulting from the attachment of a glycosyl group to a non-acyl group RO-, RS-, RSe-, etc. The bond between the glycosyl group and the non-acyl group is called a glycosidic bond. By extension, the terms N-glycosides and C-glycosides are used as class names for glycosylamines and for compounds having a glycosyl group attached to a hydrocarbyl group respectively. These terms are misnomers and should not be used. The preferred terms are glycosylamines and C-glycosyl compounds, respectively.

label: glycosyl compound
description: A carbohydrate derivative arising formally from the elimination of water from a glycosidic hydroxy group and an H atom bound to an oxygen, carbon, nitrogen or sulfur atom of a separate entity.

label: dimethylmyleran
description: A methanesulfonate ester that is hexane-2,5-diol in which the hydrogens of the hydroxy groups are replaced by methanesulfonyl groups.

label: tretamine
description: A 1,3,5-triazine that has formula C9H12N6.

label: gene expression
description: The process in which a gene's sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA or circRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA or circRNA into protein. Protein maturation is included when required to form an active form of a product from an inactive precursor form.

label: organic sulfate
description: Compounds of the general formula SO3HOR where R is an organyl group

label: iodine atom
description: Chemical element with atomic number 53.

label: regulation of macromolecule metabolic process
description: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: cellular component organization or biogenesis
description: A process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.
synonyms: cellular component organization or biogenesis at cellular level

label: carboxylic ester
description: An ester of a carboxylic acid.

label: sensory perception of taste
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a gustatory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Gustation involves the direct detection of chemical composition, usually through contact with chemoreceptor cells. This is a neurological process.

label: sensory perception of chemical stimulus
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory chemical stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: 1-bromo-2-chloroethane
description: A bromoalkane that has formula C2H4BrCl.

label: N-ethyl-N-nitrosourea
description: A urea compound having ethyl and nitroso substituents in the 1-position.

label: multicellular organismal reproductive process
description: The process, occurring above the cellular level, that is pertinent to the reproductive function of a multicellular organism. This includes the integrated processes at the level of tissues and organs.
synonyms: reproductive process in a multicellular organism

label: multicellular organism reproduction
description: The biological process in which new individuals are produced by one or two multicellular organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: wound healing
description: The series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.

label: 4-amino-3-hydroxynaphthalene-1-sulfonic acid
description: An aminonaphthalene that has formula C10H9NO4S.

label: lack of fertility in offspring
description: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to make its offspring sterile.

label: fertility
description: A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: project type
description: The type of project as characterized its data content.

label: dataset data type
description: The data type content of a dataset.

label: reagent collection
description: A collection of material reagents.

label: dataset entity type
description: Term that specifies the dataset component type.

label: dataset descriptor
description: Term that describes a dataset.

label: assay
description: Quantitative or qualitative assessment of biological source material to measure some attribute.

label: result
description: Analysis of raw data generated by an assay(s) that makes some conclusion.

label: project
description: A set of biological data from a single study. Corresponds to the NCBI bioproject, GEO series or SRA study.

label: rhythmic process
description: Any process pertinent to the generation and maintenance of rhythms in the physiology of an organism.

label: biosample
description: Biological source material characterized by an experiment.

label: circadian rhythm
description: Any biological process in an organism that recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label: rhythmic behavior
description: The specific behavior of an organism that recur with measured regularity.

label: Stalker element activity
description: Mutation caused by the transposable activity caused by the Stalker element, a LTR retrotransposon. Mobilization is induced by the activity of the stalker element transposase.
synonyms: mutation induced by Stalker element activity

label: process group
description: Genes whose products act in a specified biological process.

label: functional group
description: Genes whose products share a common biological and/or molecular function.

label: I-element activity
description: Mutation caused by the transposable activity caused by the I-element, a non-LTR retrotransposon. The I-element is 5371 base pairs long. Mobilization is induced by the activity of the I-element transposase.

label: protein complex group
description: Genes whose protein products form a macromolecular complex (GO:0043234).

label: pathway group
description: Genes whose products act in a specified signal transduction or metabolic pathway.

label: gene or gene product group
description: Genes or gene products that are acknowledged to form a natural biological group.

label: gene complex group
description: Genes with the same location on the chromosome and whose products have a similar function.

label: group descriptor
description: Descriptor that relates aspects of the grouping of genes or gene products.

label: gene array group
description: Two or more genes contiguously arranged where the individual genes are either identical in sequence, or essentially so (SO:0005851).

label: 5-bromouridine
description: A uridine having a bromo substituent at the 5-position.

label: phiC31 integrase
description: Sequence change caused by a site specific recombination catalyzed by the serine recombinase phiC31 integrase that recognizes a minimal high-efficiency attP recognition site of 39 base pairs and a minimal high-efficiency attB recognition site of 34 base pairs. The attP and attB sites contain imperfect inverted repeats flanking a short recombination core (TTG) that provides directionality.
synonyms: change induced by phiC31 integrase recombination

label: locomotor rhythm
description: The rhythm of the locomotor activity of an organism during its 24 hour activity cycle.

label: 5-bromouracil
description: A pyrimidine having keto groups at the 2- and 4-positions and a bromo group at the 5-position.

label: rate
description: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

label: coordination entity
description: An assembly consisting of a central atom (usually metallic) to which is attached a surrounding array of other groups of atoms (ligands).

label: TALEN
description: Sequence change caused by the cleavage of specific DNA sequences by transcription activator-like effector nucleases (TALENs). TALEN proteins comprise a DNA binding domain fused to the catalytic domain of the FokI endonuclease. The DNA binding domain contains a repetitive region within the middle of the protein, consisting of tandem repeats of 34 amino acid segments, with each of these segments recognizing a single base pair. The specificity of the binding is determined by two hypervariable amino acids in positions 12 and 13 (repeat-variable diresidues). Cleavage requires dimerization of FokI. The endonuclease is directed to a target region by a pair of TALENs which bind to adjacent sequences separated by a spacer region, allowing dimerization and promoting cleavage.
synonyms: change induced by TALE endonuclease cleavage

label: CRISPR/Cas9
description: Sequence change caused by a cleavage of a specific DNA sequence induced by CRISPR (clustered regularly interspaced short palindromic repeats)/Cas9 nuclease system. This system relies on the transcription of a chimeric guide RNA (gRNA) which directs the Cas9 endonuclease to a specified DNA sequence through basepairing to 20 nucleotide CRISPR target sites. These sites are located next to a 3 nucleotide protospacer adjacent motif (PAM) required for DNA cleavage.
synonyms: change induced by CRISPR/Cas9 endonuclease cleavage

label: exacerbates
description: Makes a condition worse.

label: disease qualifier
description: Qualifier that describes aspects of genetic models of disease.

label: model of
description: Characteristics associated with a given condition recapitulated in a different system.

label: DOES NOT exacerbate
description: Contrary to expectation, does not make a condition worse.

label: DOES NOT model
description: Contrary to expectation, characteristics associated with a given condition are not recapitulated in a different system.

label: ameliorates
description: Makes a condition better.

label: DOES NOT ameliorate
description: Contrary to expectation, does not make a condition better.

label: isoquinoline alkaloid
description: Any alkaloid that has a structure based on an isoquinoline nucleus. They are derived from the amino acids like tyrosine and phenylalanine.

label: heterobicyclic compound
description: A bicyclic compound in which at least one of the rings contains at least one skeletal heteroatom.

label: cognition
description: The operation of the mind by which an organism becomes aware of objects of thought or perception; it includes the mental activities associated with thinking, learning, and memory.

label: neurological system process
description: A organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of neurological system.

label: fertile
description: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: sterile
description: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: macromolecule
description: A macromolecule is a molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: oxolanes
description: Any oxacycle having an oxolane (tetrahydrofuran) skeleton.

label: N-glycosyl compound
description: A glycosyl compound arising formally from the elimination of water from a glycosidic hydroxy group and an H atom bound to a nitrogen atom, thus creating a C-N bond.

label: amide
description: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label: multicellular organismal movement
description: Any physiological process involved in changing the position of a multicellular organism or an anatomical part of a multicellular organism.

label: eclosion rhythm defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in eclosion rhythm (GO:0008062). 'eclosion rhythm' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0008062'

label: eclosion rhythm
description: The timing of the emergence of the adult fly from its pupal case, which usually occurs at dawn.

label: learning defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in learning (GO:0007612). 'learning' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007612'

label: learning
description: Any process in an organism in which a relatively long-lasting adaptive behavioral change occurs as the result of experience.

label: memory defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in memory (GO:0007613). 'memory' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007613'

label: memory
description: The activities involved in the mental information processing system that receives (registers), modifies, stores, and retrieves informational stimuli. The main stages involved in the formation and retrieval of memory are encoding (processing of received information by acquisition), storage (building a permanent record of received information as a result of consolidation) and retrieval (calling back the stored information and use it in a suitable way to execute a given task).

label: courtship behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in courtship behavior (GO:0007619). 'courtship behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007619'

label: hyperactive
description: A phenotype consisting of increased frequency of `multicellular organismal movement` (GO:0050879) compared to wild-type.

label: pain response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to pain (GO:0048265). 'response to pain' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0048265'

label: locomotor rhythm defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in locomotor rhythm (GO:0045475). 'locomotor rhythm' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0045475'

label: hypoactive
description: A phenotype consisting of decreased frequency of `multicellular organismal movement` (GO:0050879) compared to wild-type.

label: bang sensitive
description: A phenotype exhibited following mechanical shock and consisting of a brief period of intense, uncoordinated motor activity (legs and wings flailing, abdomen coiling) followed by a prolonged period of paralysis.

label: paralytic
description: Phenotype that is a disposition to paralysis under conditions that do not cause paralysis in a wild-type animal.  Paralysis is defined as an inability to exhibit `multicellular organismal movement` (GO:0050879)

label: lacking processual parts
description: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a processual part as specified by the additional entity.

label: behavioral response to nutrient
description: Any process that results in a change in the behavior of an organism as a result of a nutrient stimulus.

label: response to nutrient
description: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nutrient stimulus.

label: short lived
description: Phenotype that is a shorter adult life-span than wild-type.

label: long lived
description: Phenotype that is a longer adult life-span than wild-type.

label: gravitaxis defective
description: Phenotype that is a change in the strong tendency, seen in wild-type Drosophila melanogaster, to climb - a behavior otherwise known as negative gravitaxis (GO:0048060 ; movement away from the source of gravity).

label: negative gravitaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism away from the source of gravity.

label: suppressor of variegation
description: Genotype g1 is a suppressor of variegation if, and only if, some genotype g2 has a variegated phenotype and the degree of variegation caused by g1g2 is less than that caused by to g2 alone.

label: modifier of variegation
description: Genotype g1 is a modifier of variegation if, and only if, some genotype g2 has a variegated phenotype and the degree of variegation caused by g1g2 is significantly different from that caused by g2 alone.

label: non-suppressor of variegation
description: Genotype g1 is a non-suppressor of variegation of the phenotype due to genotype g2 if, and only if, g2 has a variegated phenotype and the degree of variegation caused by g1g2 is not less than that caused by g2 alone.

label: auxotroph
description: A phenotype that is the inability to synthesize some organic compound that can be synthesized by wild-type animals, and that is required for normal growth and/or development.

label: non-enhancer of variegation
description: Genotype g1 is a non-enhancer of variegation of the phenotype due to genotype g2 if, and only if, g2 has a variegated phenotype and the degree of variegation caused by g1g2 is not greater than that caused by g2 alone.

label: process boundary
description: time dimension = 0.  An event is an instant.

label: organic substance metabolic process
description: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

label: male courtship behavior, veined wing vibration
description: The process during courtship where the male insect vibrates his wings. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
synonyms: male courtship behaviour, veined wing vibration

label: male courtship behavior, veined wing extension
description: The process during courtship where the male insect extends his wings. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.
synonyms: male courtship behaviour, veined wing extension

label: grandchildless
description: A phenotype in which all offspring are sterile. Typically, this is due to maternal effect sterility resulting from defects in pole cell development.

label: enhancer of variegation
description: Genotype g1 is an enhancer of variegation if, and only if, some genotype g2 has a variegated phenotype and the degree of variegation caused by g1g2 is greater than that caused by g2 alone.

label: fertile
description: A phenotype that is the ability to mate and as a result produce fertilized eggs.

label: semi-fertile
description: Phenotype that is a reduction in the proportion of fertilized eggs produced to, but only to > 50% of wild-type.

label: male fertile
description: A phenotype that is the ability of males to mate and as a result produce fertilized eggs.

label: female fertile
description: A phenotype that is the ability of females to mate and as a result produce fertilized eggs.

label: male sterile
description: A phenotype that is the inability of males to mate and produce fertilized offspring.

label: sterile
description: A phenotype that is the inability to produce a zygote.

label: male semi-sterile
description: A phenotype that is a reduction in the proportion of fertilized eggs produced by males to below 50% of wild-type.

label: semi-sterile
description: A phenotype that is a reduction in the proportion of fertilized eggs produced to below 50% of wild-type.

label: male sterile germline-dependent
description: A phenotype of male sterility due to defects in the male germline.

label: male sterile soma-dependent
description: A phenotype of male sterility due to defects in somatic cells of the testis (FBbt:00006031) or of the products of these cells.

label: shape
description: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

label: female semi-sterile
description: A phenotype that is a reduction in the proportion of fertilized eggs produced by females to below 50% of wild-type.

label: female sterile germline-dependent
description: A phenotype of female sterility due to defects in the female germline.

label: female sterile
description: A phenotype that is the inability of females to mate and produce fertilized offspring.

label: female sterile soma-dependent
description: A phenotype of female sterility due to defects in somatic cells of the ovary (FBbt:00006030), or of the products of these cells (such as eggshell).

label: increased cell size
description: Phenotype that is an increase in the size of cells compared to wild-type.

label: cell size defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in the size of cells in a whole animal or in some specific organ, tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: sensory perception of sound
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive an auditory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Sonic stimuli are detected in the form of vibrations and are processed to form a sound.

label: decreased cell size
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in the size of cells in a whole animal or in some specific organ, tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type. This phenotype is not necessarily accompanied by decreased growth of a tissue - there may be more cells in an otherwise normal volume of tissue.

label: sensory perception of smell
description: The series of events required for an organism to receive an olfactory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Olfaction involves the detection of chemical composition of an organism's ambient medium by chemoreceptors. This is a neurological process.

label: large body
description: Phenotype that is an increase in body size compared to identically raised wild-type controls.

label: body color defective
description: A phenotype that is a defect in body color compared to wild-type.

label: learning or memory
description: The acquisition and processing of information and/or the storage and retrieval of this information over time.

label: small body
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in body size compared to identically raised wild-type controls.

label: partially lethal - majority die
description: A phenotype of a population that is the death of a majority of animals in that population prior to becoming a mature adult, where mature is defined as after adult stage A3 (FBdv:00006012).

label: cell lethal
description: A phenotype that is a failure of mutant cells to survive.

label: mating
description: The pairwise union of individuals for the purpose of sexual reproduction, ultimately resulting in the formation of zygotes.

label: sexual reproduction
description: A reproduction process that creates a new organism by combining the genetic material of two organisms. It occurs both in eukaryotes and prokaryotes: in multicellular eukaryotic organisms, an individual is created anew; in prokaryotes, the initial cell has additional or transformed genetic material. In a process called genetic recombination, genetic material (DNA) originating from two different individuals (parents) join up so that homologous sequences are aligned with each other, and this is followed by exchange of genetic information. After the new recombinant chromosome is formed, it is passed on to progeny.

label: eye color defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in eye color compared to wild-type.

label: mating behavior
description: The behavioral interactions between organisms for the purpose of mating, or sexual reproduction resulting in the formation of zygotes.

label: courtship behavior
description: The behavioral interactions between organisms for the purpose of attracting sexual partners.

label: partially lethal - majority live
description: A phenotype of a population that is the death of some significant proportion of animals in that population, but less that half, prior to becoming a mature adult, where mature is defined as after adult stage A3 (FBdv:00006012).

label: viable
description: A phenotype that is survival to mature adulthood, where mature is defined as after adult stage A3 (FBdv:00006012).

label: fast
description: Qualifier that describes an electrophoretic migration of a gene product that is intermediate in speed compared to the wild-type.

label: qualitative qualifier
description: Qualifier that describes a particular quality of an observable phenotype.

label: intermediate
description: Qualifier that describes a phenotype that is intermediate in speed compared to the wild-type.

label: grooming behavior
description: The specific behavior of an organism relating to grooming, cleaning and brushing to remove dirt and parasites.

label: wild-type
description: The canonical phenotype of a wild-type Drosophilid.

label: poor
description: Qualifier that describes a phenotype that has poor penetrance or expressivity.

label: reduced
description: Qualifier that describes a phenotype that has reduced penetrance or expressivity when compared to wild-type.

label: slow
description: Qualifier that describes an electrophoretic migration of a gene product that is slower than the wild-type.

label: partially
description: Incomplete penetrance or expressivity of a phenotype or incomplete suppression of a phenotype.

label: flavonoids
description: Any organic molecular entity whose stucture is based on derivatives of a phenyl-substituted 1-phenylpropane possessing a C15 or C16 skeleton, or such a structure which is condensed with a C6-C3 lignan precursors. The term is a 'superclass' comprising all members of the classes of flavonoid, isoflavonoid, neoflavonoid, chalcones, dihydrochalcones, aurones, pterocarpan, coumestans, rotenoid, flavonolignan, and flavonoid oligomers. Originally restricted to natural products, the term is also applied to synthetic compounds related to them.

label: visual behavior
description: The behavior of an organism in response to a visual stimulus.

label: feeding behavior
description: Behavior associated with the intake of food.

label: optokinetic behavior
description: The behavior of an organism pertaining to movement of the eyes and of objects in the visual field, as in nystagmus.

label: germline clone
description: A clone of germline cells that share a genotype.

label: clone of cells
description: A clone of cells that share a genotype.

label: melphalan
description: A phenylalanine derivative comprising L-phenylalanine having [bis(2-chloroethyl)amino group at the 4-position on the phenyl ring.

label: chemosensory behavior
description: Behavior that is dependent upon the sensation of chemicals.

label: flavonoid
description: Any 1-benzopyran with an aryl substituent at position 2. The term was originally restricted to natural products, but is now also used to describe semi-synthetic and fully synthetic compounds.

label: segment polarity expression pattern
description: Qualifier that describes an expression pattern of a segment polarity gene. Expression is observed in a specific location in each segment.

label: dorsal/ventral axis specification defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in dorsal/ventral axis specification (GO:0009950). 'dorsal/ventral axis specification' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0009950'

label: neurogenic phenotype
description: A phenotype that is an expansion of the developing embryonic nervous system at the expense of developing ventral epidermis.

label: meiotic cell cycle
description: Progression through the phases of the meiotic cell cycle, in which canonically a cell replicates to produce four offspring with half the chromosomal content of the progenitor cell via two nuclear divisions.

label: terminal expression pattern
description: Expression in the terminal regions of the embryo/larva: the acron, telson and adjacent segments.

label: decreased sensitivity of a process
description: A sensitivity of a process which is lower than normal or average.

label: increased sensitivity of a process
description: A sensitivity of a process which is higher than normal or average.

label: electrophoretic variant
description: Phenotype that is a difference in electrophoretic migration of a gene product compared to wild-type.

label: sex determination
description: Any process that establishes and transmits the specification of sexual status of an individual organism.

label: chemical resistant
description: Phenotype that is a decreased sensitivity (compared to wild-type) to the toxic effects of some specified chemical. The phrase 'toxic effects' here refers to reversible effects such as inebriation and sedation as well as sustained damage, developmental defects and death.

label: cytokinesis defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in cytokinesis (GO:0000910). 'cytokinesis' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0000910'

label: cytokinesis
description: The division of the cytoplasm and the plasma membrane of a cell and its partitioning into two daughter cells.

label: neurophysiology defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in the electrophysiological properties of some class of neurons, muscles or anatomical structure of the nervous system. Examples of these phenotypes at the neuron class level include defects in spontaneous or evoked excitatory junction potential. Examples at a more gross anatomical level include abnormal retinal electrophysiology (e.g.- measured by an electroretinogram).

label: neuroanatomy defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in nervous system (FBbt:00005093). 'nervous system' is defined as: '$sub_FBbt:00005093'

label: sex-determination defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sex determination (GO:0007530). 'sex determination' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007530'

label: cell polarity defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in the asymmetric distribution of components within a cell. For example an epithelial cell is 'cell polarity defective' if it lacks the normal asymmetric distribution of proteins or cell components such as junctions or villi along its apical-basal axis.

label: meiotic cell cycle defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in meiotic cell cycle (GO:0051321). 'meiotic cell cycle' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0051321'

label: extra or missing processual parts
description: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processual parts.

label: polyatomic ion
description: An ion consisting of more than one atom.

label: decreased cell death
description: Phenotype that is a decrease in the amount of cell death in a whole animal or in some specific organ tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: cell death defective
description: Phenotype that is a change in the amount of cell death in a whole animal or in some specific organ tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type. This may be due to effects on the regulation of cell death (GO:0010941) or in cell death (GO:0008219) pathways themselves.

label: sodium fluoride
description: A metal fluoride salt with a Na(+) counterion.

label: cell shape defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in the shape (PATO:0000052) of some cell compared to wild-type.

label: cisplatin
description: A platinum-containing anticancer drug that interacts with, and forms cross-links between, DNA and proteins. It is used as a neoplasm inhibitor to treat solid tumours, primarily of the testis and ovary.

label: photoperiod response variant
description: Phenotype that is a defect in entrainment of circadian clock by photoperiod (GO:0043153), which is defined as: '$sub_GO:0043153'

label: DNA repair defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in DNA repair (GO:0006281). 'DNA repair' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006281'

label: DNA repair
description: The process of restoring DNA after damage. Genomes are subject to damage by chemical and physical agents in the environment (e.g. UV and ionizing radiations, chemical mutagens, fungal and bacterial toxins, etc.) and by free radicals or alkylating agents endogenously generated in metabolism. DNA is also damaged because of errors during its replication. A variety of different DNA repair pathways have been reported that include direct reversal, base excision repair, nucleotide excision repair, photoreactivation, bypass, double-strand break repair pathway, and mismatch repair pathway.

label: increased cell death
description: Phenotype that is an increase in the amount of cell death in a whole animal or in some specific organ tissue or clone of cells compared to wild-type.

label: dosage compensation
description: Compensating for the variation in the unpaired sex chromosome:autosome chromosome ratios between sexes by activation or inactivation of genes on one or both of the sex chromosomes.

label: grooming behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in grooming behavior (GO:0007625). 'grooming behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007625'

label: touch response defective
description: Phenotype that is reduction in or loss of a stereotypical behavioral response to touch.

label: male courtship behavior
description: The behavior of a male, for the purpose of attracting a sexual partner. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: feeding behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in feeding behavior (GO:0007631). 'feeding behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007631'

label: uncoordinated
description: Phenotype that is a lack of normal co-ordination in locomotor activity.

label: flight defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in flight (GO:0060361). 'flight' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0060361'

label: flightless
description: Phenotype that is the absence of flight (GO:0060361). 'flight' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0060361'

label: visual behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in visual behavior (GO:0007632). 'visual behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007632'

label: optomotor response defective
