description: Phenotype that is a defect in optomotor response: a motor response during flight or walking that serves to stabilize both image formation on the retina and locomotor course.

label: phototaxis defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in phototaxis (GO:0042331). 'phototaxis' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0042331'

label: phototaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to light.

label: heat stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to heat (GO:0009408). 'response to heat' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0009408'

label: osmotic stress response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in response to osmotic stress (GO:0006970). 'response to osmotic stress' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006970'

label: organism emergence from protective structure
description: The developmental process in which an organism emerges from a surrounding protective structure such as an egg or pupa case.

label: smell perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception of smell (GO:0007608). 'sensory perception of smell' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007608'

label: taste perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception of taste (GO:0050909). 'sensory perception of taste' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0050909'

label: tarsal response defective
description: Phenotype that is a failure to exhibit proboscis extension reflex in response to a sugar stimulus via taste sensilla on the tarsus.

label: auditory perception defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in sensory perception of sound (GO:0007605). 'sensory perception of sound' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0007605'

label: mating rhythm defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in circadian mating behavior (GO:0035648). 'circadian mating behavior' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0035648'

label: circadian mating behavior
description: The fluctuation in mating behavior that occurs over an approximately 24 hour cycle.

label: anion
description: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

label: song defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in male courtship behavior, veined wing generated song production (GO:0045433). This is defined as '$sub_GO:0045433'

label: male courtship behavior, veined wing generated song production
description: The process during wing vibration where the male insect produces a species-specific acoustic signal called a love song.
synonyms: male courtship behaviour, veined wing generated song production

label: cellular component organization
description: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.
synonyms: cellular component organisation at cellular level

label: gravitaxis
description: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to gravity.

label: DNA metabolic process
description: Any cellular metabolic process involving deoxyribonucleic acid. This is one of the two main types of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from one, or more commonly, two, strands of linked deoxyribonucleotides.

label: polyatomic anion
description: An anion consisting of more than one atom.

label: expression clustering
description: The analysis of a gene expression profiles to define sets of genes that share similar expression characteristics.

label: result type
description: The type of result as characterized by its data content.

label: expression cluster
description: A result that represents a set of genes that share similar expression characteristics across some set of conditions.

label: binding site identification
description: An analysis that results in the identification of discrete DNA or RNA binding sites.

label: differential gene expression analysis
description: An analysis that results from the comparison of expression profiles for different conditions to identify genes that are regulated by those conditions.

label: exon junction identification
description: An analysis that results in the identification of discrete exon junctions.

label: editing site identification
description: An analysis that results in the identification of discrete A-to-I RNA editing sites.

label: TSS identification
description: An analysis that results in the identification of discrete transcription start site regions.

label: poly(A) site identification
description: An analysis that results in the identification of discrete polyadenylation sites.

label: genome binding profile
description: A result that profiles the genome occupancy for some factor.

label: mRNA translation profile
description: A result of Ribo-seq analysis that profiles ribosome protected sequences along the genome.

label: membrane invagination
description: The infolding of a membrane.

label: membrane organization
description: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a membrane. A membrane is a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

label: RNA-seq profile
description: A result that profiles expressed RNA-seq sequences along genome.

label: reference genome assembly
description: The result of extensive sequence alignment and merging to produce a genome assembly that serves as the current reference for a particular organism.

label: gene expression profile
description: A result that provides the expression values for all (or some subset) of genes in a given biological sample.

label: whole genome shotgun assembly
description: A result in which a collection of whole genome shotgun sequences is combined to build successively larger contigs.

label: genome assembly
description: The result of reconstruction of the genome achieved by aligning and merging smaller fragments.

label: genetic map
description: A result that maps the relative position of genetic markers, where distances are measured by recombination frequency.

label: physical map
description: A result that maps the relative position of genes and other sequence landmarks.

label: whole genome shotgun sequencing
description: An assay of genomic sequence that generates a large number of random genomic sequences, typically derived from paired-end sequencing of genomic fragments, that together give a complete (albeit scrambled) representation of the entire genome.

label: assay type
description: The type of assay as characterized by its data content.

label: comparative genomic hybridization by array
description: An assay that characterizes copy number variation of the genome in a sample using genome tiling array.

label: biological regulation
description: Any process that modulates a measurable attribute of any biological process, quality or function.

label: deficiency screen
description: An assay that uses a panel of deficiencies to systematically delete large segments of the genome to identify those segments that are involved in some biological process.

label: genetic screen
description: An assay that uses a large set of mutations to identify genes that are involved in some biological process.

label: two hybrid screen
description: An assay that tests proteins pairwise for interaction by fusing each to separate, complementary domains of some protein, usually a transcription factor. Upon interaction, the proximity of the complementary domains generates reporter activity.

label: RNAi screen
description: An assay that uses a panel of RNA interference (RNAi) reagents to systematically knockdown a large set of genes, one at a time, to identify those that are involved in some biological process.

label: metabolite mass spectrometry
description: An assay that identifies and characterizes small metabolites by mass spectrometry.

label: affinity purification and mass spectrometry
description: An assay that identifies the molecules that interact with a particular bait factor by mass spectrometry.

label: lipid mass spectrometry
description: An assay that identifies and characterizes lipids by mass spectrometry.

label: carbohydrate mass spectrometry
description: An assay that identifies and characterizes complex carbohydrates by mass spectrometry.

label: short RNA-Seq
description: An assay characterizing of small RNA species 17-35 nt in size by high-throughput sequencing.

label: protein mass spectrometry
description: An assay that identifies and characterizes of proteins and their post-translational modifications by mass spectrometry.

label: RNA tiling array
description: Measurement of transcribed regions across the genome by hybridization of cDNA to an oligonucleotide array, in which the genome is represented by oligonucleotides at regularly spaced intervals.

label: RNA expression microarray
description: Measurement of global transcript abundance by hybridization of cDNA to an oligonucleotide array, in which the array contains a set of probes designed with complementarity to each annotated transcript.

label: RNA-Seq
description: A quantitative method for mapping transcribed regions, in which complementary DNA fragments are subjected to high-throughput sequencing.

label: Ribo-Seq
description: Ribosome profiling, an assay in which mRNA fragments protected by ribosomes are isolated and characterized by high-throughput sequencing.

label: RIP-Seq
description: An assay in which a factor is immunoprecipitated and the associated RNA sequences are characterized by high-throughput sequencing.

label: RAMPAGE-Seq
description: An assay of 5'-capped transcripts using the orthogonal approaches of reverse transcriptase template-switching and cap-trapping, with subsequent characterization by high-throughput sequencing.

label: Repli-Seq
description: An assay mapping genomic replication patterns by labeling newly synthesized DNA in vivo with 5-bromo-2-deoxyuridine (BrdU), with subsequent affinity purification and characterization by high-throughput sequencing.

label: MNase-chip
description: An assay that maps nucleosome positions by using micrococcal nuclease to cleave linker DNA with the subsequent isolation of mononucleosomal DNA fragments that are characterized by genome tiling array.

label: MNase-Seq
description: An assay that maps nucleosome positions by using micrococcal nuclease to cleave linker DNA with the subsequent isolation of mononucleosomal DNA fragments that are characterized by high-throughput sequencing.

label: GRO-Seq
description: An assay that maps the genome-wide position, orientation and amount of transcriptionally engaged RNA polymerase by global run-on sequencing.

label: biomacromolecule
description: A macromolecule formed by a living organism.

label: DNAse-Seq
description: An assay that characterizes the genome's DNase hypersensitivity using high-throughput sequencing.

label: FAIRE-Seq
description: An assay that characterizes transcriptional regulatory elements using formaldehyde-assisted isolation of regulatory elements (FAIRE) and high-throughput sequencing.

label: copper(2+) sulfate
description: A metal sulfate compound having copper(2+) as the counterion.

label: DamID-Seq
description: A genome binding assay of some protein as characterized by creating a fusion to DNA adenine methyltransferase and analysis of methylated DNA sequences by high-throughput sequencing.

label: DNAse-chip
description: An assay that characterizes the genome's DNase hypersensitivity using genome tiling array.

label: CLiP-Seq
description: An RNA binding assay of some protein as characterized by cross-linking immunoprecipitation (CLiP) and high-throughput sequencing of co-purifying RNA fragments.

label: DamID-chip
description: A genome binding assay of some protein as characterized by creating a fusion to DNA adenine methyltransferase and analysis of methylated DNA sequences by genome tiling array.

label: ChIP-chip
description: A genome binding assay of some factor as characterized by chromatin immunoprecipitation (ChIP) of that factor and analysis of co-purifying DNA fragments using genome tiling array.

label: ChIP-Seq
description: A genome binding assay of some factor as characterized by chromatin immunoprecipitation (ChIP) of that factor and high-throughput sequencing of co-purifying DNA fragments.

label: 2,5-bis(aziridin-1-yl)-1,4-benzoquinone
description: A member of the class of benzoquinones that is 1,4-benzoquinone in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 5 are replaced by aziridin-1-yl groups.

label: CAGE-Seq
description: An assay of 5' capped transcripts, using CAGE to biotinylate and isolate the 7-methylguanosine cap, with subsequent characterization by high-throughput sequencing.

label: male mating behavior
description: The specific behavior of a male organism that is associated with reproduction.

label: immortalized cell line
description: A biosample consisting of cells isolated from animal tissue that have acquired the ability to proliferate indefinitely.

label: biosample type
description: The type of biosample as characterized by its biological source material.

label: isolated cells
description: A biosample containing dissociated cells isolated from the organism, typically isolated by affinity capture or sorting methods.

label: primary cell line
description: A biosample consisting of cells that were isolated from animal tissue and cultured in vitro for a limited amount of time.

label: whole organism
description: A biosample that comprises the whole animal.

label: tissue
description: A biosample derived from a multicellular structure comprising similar cells with some specific function, typically isolated by dissection.

label: other
description: A project type that is not described by other more specific terms.

label: phylogenetic analysis
description: A project that reconstructs the evolutionary history of a group of genes or organisms.

label: reagent
description: A project that describes a large material resource that is accessible to the community.

label: gene model annotation
description: A project that constructs models describing the set of transcripts and polypeptides encoded by some group of genes.

label: hyperplastic
description: A increased size quality inhering in an organ or tissue by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting increased number of cells.

label: d-block molecular entity
description: A d-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a d-block element.

label: phenotypic screen
description: A project that searches for the genes responsible for a particular observable trait.

label: chemical screen
description: A project that searches for chemicals, natural or synthetic, that elicit some biological effect.

label: interactome
description: A project that characterizes the set of inter-molecular interactions in an organism.

label: metabolome
description: A project that characterizes the set of small molecules in an organism.

label: transcriptome
description: A project that characterizes the set of transcribed RNA sequences expressed by the genome.

label: proteome
description: A project that characterizes the set of proteins expressed in an organism.

label: genome variation
description: A project that characterizes the intraspecific variation of an organism's genome.

label: genome binding
description: A project that characterizes the occupancy profile of a factor that binds directly or indirectly to the genome.

label: umbrella project
description: A project that groups together related sub-projects.

label: genome
description: A project that characterizes an organism's genome sequence.

label: interspecific hybrid
description: A sample that is derived from a controlled mating between individuals of two specific species.

label: mated
description: A sample in which the individuals have undergone mating.

label: trait selection
description: An inbred strain is subjected to artificial laboratory selection of some trait over the course of several generations.

label: artificial
description: A biosample that was synthesized in a laboratory.

label: biosample scope
description: The scope and purity of a biosample, ranging from single cell to environmental sample.

label: wild caught
description: A sample that originated from a wild caught population and is considered true wild type.

label: multispecies sample
description: A biosample that is derived from multiple species.

label: environmental
description: A biosample derived from an environmental sample for which the species content is unknown.

label: single individual sample
description: A biosample that is derived from one individual.

label: multi-individual sample
description: A biosample that is derived from multiple individuals.

label: cell motility
description: Any process involved in the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that results in translocation of the cell from one place to another.

label: localization of cell
description: Any process in which a cell is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.
synonyms: establishment and maintenance of cell localization

label: single cell sample
description: A biosample that is derived from only a single cell.

label: chemical stimulus study
description: A project study design investigating the effects of a chemical stimulus on some aspect of an organism.

label: study design
description: The aim of the project investigation, as defined by the key variables in the set of experiments.

label: physical stimulus study
description: A project study design investigating the effects of a physical stimulus on some aspect of an organism.

label: gene study
description: A project study design in which the goal of the study is to examine properties of a specific gene or set of genes.

label: biotic stimulus study
description: A project study design investigating the effects of a biotic stimulus on some aspect of an organism.

label: cell type study
description: A project study design involving the use of cultured or extracted cells with an investigative focus of studying a cellular property.

label: subcellular component study
description: A project study design examining subcellular components of cells including organelles, the nucleus, or any other grouping of intra- or extracellular material.

label: tissue type study
description: A project study design investigating the biological mechanisms of intact or dissected tissues in order to understand their form or function.

label: circadian rhythm study
description: A project study design investigating the biological mechanisms responsible for the control or maintenance of circadian rhythm.

label: cell cycle study
description: A project study design investigating the biological mechanisms of the cell responsible for maintaining or controlling aspects of the cell cycle.

label: sex study
description: A project study design that aims to characterize the biological mechanisms responsible for the development or maintenance of the sex-related properties of an organism.

label: 20-30% egg length
description: 20-30% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: developmental stage study
description: A project study design investigating the biological mechanisms responsible for the control or maintenance of development.

label: species study
description: A project study design that aims to compare different species.

label: strain study
description: A project study design that aims to compare different wild-type strains for a given species.

label: project attribute
description: A descriptor that describes some aspect of a project.

label: 10-90% egg length
description: 10-90% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 100% egg length
description: At the anterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: microarray library
description: A collection of hybridization targets on a microarray.

label: reagent collection type
description: The type of reagent collection as characterized by the material resources comprised by the collection.

label: 20% egg length
description: 10% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 20-100% egg length
description: 20-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-50% egg length
description: 10-50% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-60% egg length
description: 10-60% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-70% egg length
description: 10-70% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-80% egg length
description: 10-80% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-40% egg length
description: 10-40% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: TE insertion stock collection
description: A collection of transposable element insertions available as fly stocks.

label: fly strain collection
description: A collection of wild-type fly strains.

label: transgenic insertion collection
description: A collection of transgenic construct insertions available as fly stocks.

label: RNAi construct collection
description: A collection of transgenic constructs, available as fly stocks, designed to target gene knockdown by RNA-interference.

label: 10-20% egg length
description: 10-20% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: genomic clone collection
description: A collection of genomic DNA clones available as plasmids. This may include BAC, YAC, fosmid, cosmid and P1 clone collections.

label: 10-30% egg length
description: 10-30% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: construct collection
description: A collection of transgenic constructs that are available as fly stocks.

label: dsRNA amplicon collection
description: A collection of PCR products used for the synthesis of double-stranded RNA to induce RNA-interference.

label: allele collection
description: A collection of alleles that are available as fly stocks.

label: 0-80% egg length
description: 0-80% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: cDNA library
description: A collection of cDNAs available as plasmids.

label: 0-90% egg length
description: 0-90% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10% egg length
description: 10% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 10-100% egg length
description: 10-100% of egg length from the posterior tip (0%) of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: aberration stock collection
description: A collection of large chromosomal aberrations, available as fly stocks, which may include duplications, deletions, inversions or translocations.

label: 0-40% egg length
description: 0-40% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 0-50% egg length
description: 0-50% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 0-60% egg length
description: 0-60% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 0-70% egg length
description: 0-70% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: analysis
description: A result that is produced from the detailed examination of data to come to some conclusion.

label: genomic copy number profile
description: A result that represents the copy number variation across the genome for a given sample.

label: liftover file
description: A result that represents the mapping of coordinates between two different genome assemblies for a given species.

label: metabolite profile
description: A result that represents a set of small molecules identified for a given sample.

label: 0-100% egg length
description: The full length of the pre-gastrula embryo.

label: phenotypic profile
description: A result that represents the range of phenotypes obtained for a set of genetic perturbations.

label: 0-20% egg length
description: 0-20% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: RNA-protein interaction
description: A result that represents a set of RNA-protein interactions for a given sample.

label: 0-30% egg length
description: 0-30% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: RNA-RNA interaction
description: A result that represents a set of RNA-RNA interactions for a given sample.

label: gene list
description: A result that represents a set of genes that have some shared characteristic.

label: protein-protein interaction
description: A result that represents a set of protein-protein interactions for a given sample.

label: 0% egg length
description: At the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: 0-10% egg length
description: 0-10% of egg length from the posterior tip of the egg or pre-gastrula embryo.

label: ventral
description: Restricted to ventral region of some specified type.

label: ventro-lateral
description: Restricted to ventro-lateral region of some specified type.

label: proximal
description: Restricted to proximal region of some specified type.

label: restricted
description: Restricted to unknown part(s) of a specified type.

label: supernumerary
description: Present in the correct location but in larger numbers than in wild-type.

label: structural qualifier
description: Qualifier used to describe the appearance of extra copies of an anatomical structure.

label: ubiquitous
description: Expressed everywhere at some specified stage.

label: lateral
description: Restricted to lateral region(s) of some specified type.

label: medial
description: Restricted to medial region of some specified type.

label: posterior
description: Restricted to posterior region of some specified type.

label: N-methyl-N'-nitro-N-nitrosoguanidine
description: An N-nitroguanidine compound having nitroso and methyl substituents at the N'-position

label: dorso-lateral
description: Restricted to dorso-lateral region of some specified type.

label: ectopic
description: When, compared to wild-type, an extra copy of an anatomical structure is present in an abnormal location, then this structure is ectopic.

label: dorsal
description: Restricted to dorsal region of some specified type.

label: basal
description: Restricted to basal region of some specified type.

label: central
description: Restricted to central region of some specified type.

label: distal
description: Restricted to distal region of some specified type.

label: segment boundary
description: Present in the area that separates segments.

label: anterior
description: Restricted to anterior region of some specified type.

label: apical
description: Restricted to apical region of some specified type.

label: behavioral quality
description: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

label: hatching
description: The emergence of an immature organism from a protective structure.

label: HBL1 supplied transposase
description: Mutation caused by the activity of the hobo element, mobilized by an hobo transposase which is produced from the supplied P-element helper plasmid HBL1.
synonyms: mutation induced by Hobo transposase source HBL1

label: hobo activity
description: Mutation induced by the transposable activity caused by hobo, a DNA transposable element. The hobo element is 3.0 kilobases in length with 12 base pairs inverted terminal repeats. After mobilization by the hobo transposase and upon insertion it generates a flanking duplication of 8 base pairs at the target site upon insertion.
synonyms: mutation induced by hobo element activity

label: MRF23.5 induced male recombination
description: Mutation caused by a male recombination event induced by a male recombination factor which is present in chromosomes extracted from a population in Patras, Greece.
synonyms: mutation induced by MRF23.5 male recombination

label: male recombination induced by dysgenesis
description: Mutation caused by PM hybrid dysgenesis that is induced by the higher frequency of recombination in certain male chromosomes.

label: MRF31.1 induced male recombination
description: Mutation caused by a male recombination event induced by a male recombination factor which is present in chromosomes extracted from a population in Patras, Greece.
synonyms: mutation induced by MRF31.1 male recombination

label: hobo dysgenesis
description: Mutation caused by hybrid dysgenesis that results from the mobilization of the hobo element.

label: p pi25.7wc
description: Mutation caused by the mobilization of a P-element by the transposase produced from the helper plasmid p pi25.7wc. This plasmid is a P-element from which the 3' terminus has been deleted, making it unable to integrate into the host's DNA. It has an additional 23 base pairs deletion of the 3' terminus compared to p pi25.1.
synonyms: mutation induced by P-element mobilization by p pi25.7wc supplied transposase

label: P-element activity
description: Mutation induced by the transposable activity caused by a P-element, a DNA transposable element. The P-element is 2.9 kilobases in length with 31 base pairs inverted terminal repeats. Upon insertion it generates a flanking duplication of 8 base pairs at the target site upon insertion. Mobilization is induced by the activity of a P-element transposase.

label: PM hybrid dysgenesis
description: Mutation caused by hybrid dysgenesis that results from the action of the P-element.
synonyms: mutation induced by PM hybrid dysgenesis

label: MRh12 induced male recombination
description: Mutation caused by a male recombination event induced by a male recombination factor which is present in chromosomes extracted from a population in Haifa, Israel.
synonyms: mutation induced by  MRh12 male recombination

label: MRT007 induced male recombination
description: Mutation caused by a male recombination event in the second and third chromosomes induced by a male recombination factor which is present in chromosomes extracted from a population in Harlingen, Texas.
synonyms: mutation induced by MRT007 male recombination

label: p pi25.1 supplied transposase
description: Mutation caused by the mobilization of a P-element by the transposase produced from the helper plasmid p pi25.1. This plasmid is a P-element from which the 3' terminus has been deleted, making it unable to integrate into the host's DNA. It is missing a 23 base pairs deletion of the 3' terminus compared to p pi25.1wc.
synonyms: mutation induced by P-element mobilization by p pi25.1 supplied transposase

label: Delta2-3 transposase
description: Mutation induced by the mobilization of a P-element by the Delta2-3 transposase. The source of Delta2-3 is a stable genomic integration from which the third intron has been deleted.
synonyms: mutation induced by P-element mobilization by Delta2-3 transposase

label: jumpstarter activity
description: Mutation caused by a P-element that is inserted into the genome and that is used to create more insertions at other sites.

label: IR-hybrid dysgenesis
description: Mutation caused by hybrid dysgenesis that results from the mobilization of the I-element retrotransposon.

label: Stalker-hybrid dysgenesis
description: Mutation induced by hybrid dysgenesis caused by the mobilization of the Stalker transposable element.

label: thermotaxis behavior defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in thermotaxis (GO:0043052). 'thermotaxis' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0043052'

label: I-SceI
description: Sequence change caused by the cleavage of an 18 base pair DNA sequence by the I-SceI endonuclease.
synonyms: change induced by I-SceI endonuclease cleavage

label: cre recombinase
description: Sequence change induced by a site specific recombination event catalyzed by the tyrosine recombinase cre. Recombination is induced between two 34 base pairs loxP sites. These consist of two 13 base pair perfect inverted repeats flanking an 8 base pair asymmetric spacer that confers directionality.
synonyms: change induced by cre recombinase recombination

label: segregation
description: Sequence change induced by chromosomal segregation.

label: cellular localization
description: A cellular localization process whereby a substance or cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within a cell including the localization of substances or cellular entities to the cell membrane.
synonyms: establishment and maintenance of cellular localization

label: establishment of localization in cell
description: Any process, occuring in a cell, that localizes a substance or cellular component. This may occur via movement, tethering or selective degradation.

label: hesperidin
description: A disaccharide derivative that consists of hesperetin substituted by a 6-O-(alpha-L-rhamnopyranosyl)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl moiety at position 7 via a glycosidic linkage.

label: reduction
description: Mutation caused by a recombination event between tandem repeats of rRNA genes that causes unequal chromatid exchange at crossing over and a reduction in the number of functional copies. It leads to an aggravation of phenotype, in the case of a mutation causing a change from a wildtype to mutant phenotype or a change from a mutant to a more severe mutant phenotype.

label: endocytosis defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in endocytosis (GO:0006897). 'endocytosis' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006897'

label: FLPase
description: Sequence change caused by a site specific recombination event catalyzed by the tyrosine recombinase FLPase, that recognizes minimal FLP recombination target (FRT) sites of 34 base pairs. For site specific integration, the recombination site consists of 48 base pairs containing an additional isolated base pair and a third 13 base pair direct repeat.

label: unequal recombination
description: Sequence change caused by a recombination event that causes an unequal exchange of genetic material between homologous or non-homologous regions.

label: mitotic recombination
description: Sequence change caused by the exchange of genetic material during mitosis that occurs at crossing over, and more frequently between homologous chromosomes.

label: magnification
description: Sequence change caused by a recombination event between tandem repeats of rRNA genes that causes unequal chromatid exchange at crossing over and an increase in the number of functional copies. It causes a reversion from mutant to wild-type phenotype.

label: detachment
description: Mutation that is caused by a recombination event that causes the breakdown of compound chromosome arms resulting in duplications or deletions in proximal regions.

label: gene conversion
description: Sequence change caused by a DNA recombination process that results in the unidirectional transfer of genetic material from a donor sequence to a highly homologous acceptor (GO:0035822).

label: intralocus exchange
description: Mutation caused by a recombination event that causes the unequal exchange of small intralocus regions, usually leading to the formation of duplication and deficiency products.

label: temperature
description: Mutation caused by exposure to a temperature that is higher or lower than 25 degrees Celsius.

label: cold
description: Mutation induced by exposure to temperature that is lower than 25 degrees Celsius.

label: heat
description: Mutation induced by exposure to a temperature that is higher than 25 degrees Celsius.

label: spontaneous
description: Mutation caused by a spontaneous event.

label: beta-estradiol conditional
description: Phenotype expressed only in the presence of beta-estradiol (CHEBI:16469).

label: in vitro construct - amino acid replacement
description: Sequence change introduced by an in vitro construct that uses site directed mutagenesis to target a particular region of the gene resulting in a change to the change to the amino acids sequence encodes..
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - amino acid replacement

label: in vitro construct - site directed mutagenesis
description: Mutation induced by an in vitro construct that uses site directed mutagenesis to target a particular region of the gene.
synonyms: mutation induced by an in vitro construct - site directed mutagenesis

label: in vitro construct - RNAi
description: Sequence change introduced by an in vitro construct designed to generate dsRNA for RNA interference (RNAi) experiments.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - RNAi

label: in vitro construct
description: DNA change introduced by using an in vitro construct. The sequence of the in vitro construct determines the type of change.
synonyms: change induced by in vitro construct

label: natural population
description: Mutation found in a natural population.

label: in vitro construct - genomic fragment
description: Sequence change introduced by an in vitro construct containing a genomic fragment that partially or fully rescues loss of function mutations or deletions of the gene whose sequence it carries.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - genomic fragment

label: in vitro construct - minigene
description: Sequence change introduced by an in vitro construct that contains the wild-type open reading frame of a gene (without introns), the expression of which is controlled by a wild-type promoter of the same gene. Such constructs are often generated by fusing a cDNA to a genomic region containing promoter sequences, or more rarely by deletion of introns and other non-essential sequences from a genomic region, leaving a wild type coding region and promoter intact.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - minigene

label: triazines
description: Compounds based on a triazine skeleton.

label: in vitro construct - deletion
description: Sequence change introduced by an in vitro construct generated by internal deletion of some genomic sequence or cDNA.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - deletion

label: in vitro construct - regulatory fusion
description: Sequence change introduced by using an in vitro construct that contains a fusion of the regulatory region of one gene on to the coding region of another. Examples in FlyBase include heat shock constructs, FRT flip out constructs and reporter genes.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - regulatory fusion

label: in vitro construct - coding region fusion
description: Sequence change introduced by using an in vitro construct that contains a in-frame fusion of the open reading frames from two or more genes. In FlyBase, the resulting genes may be classified as fusion genes or tagged genes.
synonyms: change induced by an in vitro construct - coding region fusion

label: wound healing defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in wound healing (GO:0042060). 'wound healing' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0042060'

label: developmental rate defective
description: Phenotype that is a change in the rate of some developmental process (GO:0032502) taking place prior to mature adulthood (defined as adult stage A3), compared to wild-type. Note, developmental processes include stages in development of the whole animal (e.g.- larval development) as well as specific sub-processes, such as dorsal closure.

label: immune response defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in immune response (GO:0006955). 'immune response' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0006955'

label: methyl methanesulfonate
description: A methanesulfonate ester that has formula C2H6O3S.

label: planar polarity defective
description: Phenotype that is a defect in establishment of planar polarity (GO:0001736). 'establishment of planar polarity' is defined as: '$sub_GO:0001736'

label: hyperplasia
description: Phenotype that is an increase in size of a tissue or organ due to increased numbers of cells, where the affected tissue or organ maintains its normal form.

label: tumorigenic
description: Phenotype that is characterized by the formation of abnormal masses of tissue (tumors) as the result of neoplasia.

label: melanotic mass phenotype
description: Phenotype characterized by the formation of lumps of melanotic tissue inside the body in the absence of foreign bodies.

label: melanotic necrosis
description: Phenotype characterized by closely associated necrosis and melanization.

label: chemical sensitive
description: Phenotype that is an increased sensitivity (compared to wild-type) to the toxic effects of some specified chemical. The phrase 'toxic effects' here refers to reversible effects such as inebriation and sedation as well as sustained damage, developmental defects and death.

label: radiation resistant
description: Phenotype that is a decreased tendency for radiation exposure to cause toxic effects.

label: radiation sensitive
description: Phenotype that is an increased tendency for radiation exposure to cause toxic effects.

label: Minute
description: Dominant phenotype consisting of short slender bristles and delayed development. Homozygotes are cell lethal.
